obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4961)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1 1st July, 1956, vide notification No. S. R. O. 1456, dated 26th June, 1956, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4961&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Life Insurance Corporation`
  line `Act, 1956.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4962)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4962&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) appointed day means the date on which the Corporation is established under section 3;`
  line
  line `^1[(1a) Audit Committee means the Committee constituted under section 19C;`
  line
  line `(1b) Board of Directors or Board means the collective body of the directors appointed or`
  line `nominated or deemed as such under section 4;`
  line
  line `(1c)`
  line `Chairperson means the Chairperson referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(1d) Chief Executive means,--`
  line
  line `(i) during the initial period, the Chairperson referred to in sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ii) after the initial period, the Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director;`
  line
  line `(1e) Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director means the Chief Executive Officer`
  line `and Managing Director referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(1f) Companies Act means the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(1g) court means Court as defined in clause (29) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013;]`
  line
  line `(2) composite insurer means an insurer carrying on in addition to controlled business any other kind`
  line `of insurance business;`
  line
  line `(3) controlled business means--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of any insurer specified in sub-clause (a) (ii) or sub-clause (b) of clause (9) of`
  line `section 2 of the Insurance Act and carrying on life insurance business--`
  line
  line `(a) all his business, if he carries on no other class of insurance business;`
  line
  line `(b) all the business appertaining to his life insurance business, if he carries on any other class`
  line `of insurance business also;`
  line
  line `(c) all his business, if his certificate of registration under the Insurance Act in respect of`
  line `general insurance business stands wholly cancelled for a period of more than six months on the`
  line `19th day of January, 1956;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of any other insurer specified in clause (9) of section 2 of the Insurance Act and`
  line `carrying on life insurance business--`
  line
  line `(a) all his business in India, if he carries on no other class of insurance business in India;`
  line
  line `(b) all the business appertaining to his life insurance business in India, if he carries on any`
  line `other class of insurance business also in India;`
  line
  line `(c) all his business in India if he certificate of registration under the Insurance Act in respect`
  line `of general insurance business in India stands wholly cancelled for a period of more than six`
  line `months on the 19th day of January, 1956.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- An insurer is said to carry on no class of insurance business other than life`
  line `insurance business, if in addition to life insurance business, he carries on only capital redemption`
  line `business or annuity certain business or both; and the expression business appertaining to his life`
  line `insurance business in sub-clauses (i) and (ii) shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a provident society, as defined in section 65 of the Insurance Act, all its`
  line business;
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of the Central Government or a State Government, all life insurance business`
  line `carried on by it, subject to the exceptions specified in section 44;`
  line
  line `(4) Corporation means the Life Insurance Corporation of India established under section 3;`
  line
  line `^1[(4a) director means a director appointed or nominated or deemed as such under section 4;;`
  line
  line `(4b) financial statement, in relation to the Corporation, includes;`
  line
  line `(i) a balance-sheet as at the end of the financial year;`
  line
  line `(ii) a profit and loss account for the financial year;`
  line
  line `(iii) cash flow statement for the financial year;`
  line
  line `(iv) a statement of changes in equity, if applicable; and`
  line
  line `(v) any explanatory note annexed to, or forming part of, any document referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (i) to sub-clause (iv);;`
  line
  line `(4c) fully diluted basis shall mean, in relation to the percentage holding of the Central`
  line `Government on such basis, the total number of shares held by the Central Government expressed as a`
  line `percentage of the total number of shares of the Corporation that would be outstanding if all possible`
  line `sources of conversion are exercised;`
  line
  line `(4d) independent director means an independent director referred to in clause (g) of sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(4e) initial period means the period of three years reckoned from the date on which the`
  line `provisions of section 130 of the Finance Act, 2021 shall come into force;;`
  line
  line `(5) Insurance Act means the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938);`
  line
  line `(6) insurer means an insurer as defined in the Insurance Act who carries on life insurance business`
  line `in India and includes the Government and a provident society as defined in section 65 of the Insurance`
  line Act;
  line
  line `^1[(6a) Managing Director means a Managing Director referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `^2[(7) member means every person holding shares of the Corporation and whose name is entered in`
  line `the register of members maintained under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 5B;`
  line
  line `(7a) Nomination and Remuneration Committee means the Committee constituted under section`
  line 19B;
  line
  line `(7b) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette, and the expression notify`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;]`
  line
  line `(8) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(8a) special resolution means a resolution for which the intention to propose the same as a special`
  line `resolution has been duly specified in the notice given to members for calling a general meeting, and the`
  line `votes cast in favour of the resolution by members are not less than three times the number of votes, if any,`
  line `cast against the resolution;]`
  line
  line `(9) Tribunal means a Tribunal constituted under section 17 and having jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter under the rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^3[(10) unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context, all the words and expressions used`
  line `herein but not defined and defined in the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938) or in the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the said Acts.9563`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 129 (w.e.f.30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 129, bid., for clause (7) (w.e.f. 30-6-2021)`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 129, bid., for clause (10) (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4963)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Life Insurance Corporation of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4963&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect`
  line `from such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there`
  line `shall be established a Corporation called the Life Insurance Corporation of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal with`
  line `power subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property, and may by its name`
  line `sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4964)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Board of Directors`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 130, ibid., for section 4 (w.e.f. 29-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4964&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Board of Directors.--(1) The general superintendence and direction of the affairs and business`
  line `of the Corporation shall vest in its Board of Directors, which may exercise all such powers and do all such`
  line `acts and things as may be exercised or done by the Corporation and are not by this Act expressly directed`
  line `or required to be done by the Corporation in general meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of Directors of the Corporation shall consist of the following directors, not exceeding`
  line `eighteen, of whom at least one shall be a woman, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson of the Board, to be appointed by the Central Government, who shall,--`
  line
  line `(i) during the initial period, be a whole-time director of the Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(ii) after the initial period, be from amongst the non-executive directors nominated or to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) after the initial period, a Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director, who shall be a`
  line `whole-time director of the Corporation to be appointed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director is appointed before`
  line `expiry of the initial period, the individual holding office as Chairperson shall be deemed to have been`
  line `appointed as the Chief Executive Officer and Managing Director on and from the date of such expiry;`
  line
  line `(c) Managing Directors, not exceeding four, to be appointed by the Central Government, who`
  line `shall be whole-time directors of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(d) an officer of the Central Government not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India, to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) an individual to be nominated by the Central Government, who has special knowledge or`
  line `practical experience in actuarial science, business management, economics, finance, human resources,`
  line `information technology, insurance, law, risk management, or any other field the special knowledge or`
  line `practical experience of which would be useful to the Corporation in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government or who represent the interests of policyholders;`
  line
  line `(f) where the total holding of members other than the Central Government in the paid-up equity`
  line `capital of the Corporation is`
  line
  line `(a) not more than ten per cent., one individual;`
  line
  line `(b) more than ten per cent., two individuals,`
  line
  line `who shall be elected by and from amongst such members and in such manner as may be specified by`
  line `regulations, to be appointed by the Board; and`
  line
  line `(g) such number of independent directors, not exceeding nine, to be recommended by the`
  line `Nomination and Remuneration Committee and appointed by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) An independent director of the Corporation shall, in relation to the Corporation, meet the same`
  line `criteria of independence as an independent director of a company is required to meet in relation to the`
  line `company under sub-section (6) of section 149 of the Companies Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that such a director shall also meet, in addition to the aforesaid criteria, any criteria that the`
  line `Nomination and Renumeration Committee may formulate regarding qualifications, positive attributes and`
  line `independence:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every such director shall at the first meeting of the Board in which he`
  line `participates as a director and thereafter at the first meeting of the Board in every financial year or`
  line `whenever there is any change in the circumstances which may affect his status as an independent director,`
  line `give a declaration that he meets the criteria of independence under this sub-section and that he is not`
  line `aware of any circumstance or situation, which exist or may reasonably be anticipated, that could impair or`
  line `impact his ability to discharge his duties with an objective independent judgment and without any`
  line `external influence.`
  line
  line `(4) An individual appointed by the Board as a director under clause (f) or clause (g) of sub-section (2)`
  line `shall hold office up to the date of the next annual general meeting or the last date on which the annual`
  line `general meeting should have been held, whichever is earlier, and shall hold office beyond such date only`
  line `if his appointment is approved at the annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(5) Before an individual is appointed or nominated as a director under sub-section (2), the Central`
  line `Government or the Nomination and Remuneration Committee, as the case may be, shall satisfy itself that`
  line `such an individual as a director shall have no financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially`
  line `the exercise or performance by him of the functions of a director:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall satisfy itself from time to time with respect to every director other than`
  line `a director nominated under clause (d) of sub-section (2) that he has no such interest:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, for the purposes of this sub-section, any individual who is, or whose`
  line `appointment or nomination or election is proposed and who has consented to be a director, shall furnish`
  line `such information as the Central Government or the Nomination and Remuneration Committee or the`
  line `Board, as the case may be, may require.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), on and from the appointed date, an`
  line `individual appointed under section 4 who is eligible to be or remain a director under section 4A and who,`
  line `immediately before such appointed date, held the office of a member of the Corporation`
  line
  line `(i) in the capacity as the Chairman of the Corporation, shall be deemed to be a director and the`
  line `Chairperson under sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(ii) in the capacity as a Managing Director of the Corporation, shall be deemed to be a director`
  line `and a Managing Director under clause (c) of sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(iii) and is an officer of the Central Government not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India in the Department of Financial Services, shall be deemed to be a director`
  line `nominated under clause (d) of sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(iv) and has been in office for a duration which is the longest amongst members other than`
  line `members referred to in clauses (i), (ii) and (iii), shall be deemed to be a director nominated under`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that every such individual shall hold office until expiry of the term, if any, specified at`
  line `the time of his appointment as a member of the Corporation, or until a director appointed or`
  line `nominated, as the case may be, under sub-section (2) in place of such an individual assumes office:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any act or proceeding of the collective body of members constituting the`
  line `Corporation under section 4 before the appointed date, shall be deemed to be an act or proceeding, as`
  line `the case may be, of the Board.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, -`
  line
  line `(a) notwithstanding anything contained in clause (7) of section 2, the expression member`
  line `shall mean a member appointed to the Corporation constituted under section 4 as it stood before`
  line `the coming into force of section 130 of the Finance Act, 2021;`
  line
  line `(b) appointed date means the date on which the provisions of section 130 of the Finance`
  line `Act, 2021 shall come into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (55909)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Disqualification to be director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 130, ibid., for section 4 (w.e.f. 29-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55909&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Disqualification to be director.--An individual shall not be eligible to be or remain a director`
  line `if, --`
  line
  line `(a) he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(b) he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(c) he has applied to be adjudicated as an insolvent and his application is pending;`
  line
  line `(d) he has been convicted by a court of any offence, whether involving moral turpitude or`
  line `otherwise, and sentenced in respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months and a period`
  line `of five years has not elapsed from the date of expiry of the sentence:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an individual has been convicted of any offence and sentenced in respect thereof`
  line `to imprisonment for a period of seven years or more, he shall not be eligible to be a director;`
  line
  line `(e) an order disqualifying him to be a director has been passed by a court or the National`
  line `Company Law Tribunal constituted under section 408 of the Companies Act, and the order is in force;`
  line
  line `(f) he has not paid any calls in respect of any shares of the Corporation held by him, whether`
  line `alone or jointly with others, and six months have elapsed from the last day fixed for the payment of`
  line `such call;`
  line
  line `(g) he attracts any disqualification for being a director of a company under the provisions of subsection (2) of section 164 of the Companies Act, subject to such exceptions thereto as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(h) he is a salaried government official, other than an individual nominated director under clause`
  line `(d) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(i) he is an insurance agent or an intermediary or an insurance intermediary;`
  line
  line `(j) he is an employee of the Corporation, other than the Chief Executive or a Managing Director,`
  line `or of its subsidiary or associate company;`
  line
  line `(k) he is a director of a subsidiary or an associate company of the Corporation and is other than`
  line `the Chief Executive or a Managing Director;`
  line
  line `(l) he is an employee or a director or a promoter of any insurer carrying on life insurance business`
  line `anywhere in the world, other than the Corporation or its subsidiary or associate company, or of any`
  line `holding company, subsidiary or associate company of such an insurer;`
  line
  line `(m) he absents himself from all the meetings of the Board held during a period of twelve months,`
  line `with or without seeking leave of absence of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the disqualifications referred to in clauses (d) and (e) shall continue to apply even if`
  line `an appeal or petition has been filed against the order of conviction or disqualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (55910)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 6
  title `Disclosure of interest by director and senior management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 130, ibid., for section 4 (w.e.f. 29-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55910&sectionno=4B&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[4B. Disclosure of interest by director and senior management.--(1) Every director shall at the`
  line `first meeting of the Board in which he participates as a director and thereafter at the first meeting of the`
  line `Board in every financial year, or whenever there is any change in the disclosures already made, then at the`
  line `first Board meeting held after such change, disclose his concern or interest in any body corporate, which`
  line `shall include shareholding, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every director who is in any way, whether directly or indirectly, concerned or interested in a`
  line `contract or arrangement or proposed contract or arrangement entered into or to be entered into by the`
  line Corporation
  line
  line `(a) with a body corporate in which such director or such director in association with any other`
  line `director, holds more than two per cent. shareholding of that body corporate, or is a promoter,`
  line `manager, chief executive officer or trustee of that body corporate, or`
  line
  line `(b) with a firm or other entity in which such director is a partner, owner or member, as the case`
  line `may be, shall not participate in any meeting of the Board or of its Committee in which such contract`
  line `or arrangement is deliberated upon, or in any other deliberations or discussions regarding such`
  line `contract or arrangement, and shall, in the case of such deliberations in a meeting of the Board or its`
  line `Committee, disclose the nature of his concern or interest to the Board or the Committee, as the case`
  line `may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any director who is not so concerned or interested at the time of entering into`
  line `such contract or arrangement, he shall, if he becomes concerned or interested after the contract or`
  line `arrangement is entered into, disclose his concern or interest forthwith when he becomes concerned or`
  line `interested, or at the first meeting of the Board held after he becomes so concerned or interested.`
  line
  line `(3) A contract or arrangement entered into by the Corporation without disclosure under sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) or with participation by a director who is concerned or interested in any way, whether directly or`
  line `indirectly, in such contract or arrangement, shall be voidable at the option of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) Such employees as the Board may specify as constituting the senior management of the`
  line `Corporation shall make disclosures to the Board relating to all material, financial and commercial`
  line `transactions, in which they have personal interest that may have a potential conflict with the interest of the`
  line `Corporation, and the Board shall formulate a policy on such transactions, including any materiality`
  line `threshold therefor, and shall review such policy at least once every three years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this sub-section, conflict of interest relates to dealing in the shares`
  line `of the Corporation or any of its subsidiaries or associate companies, commercial dealings with bodies in`
  line `which the senior management individual or his relatives have shareholding, etc.`
  line
  line `(5) If an individual who is a director contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2),`
  line `or an employee referred to in sub-section (4), contravenes such provisions, such an individual or`
  line `employee shall be liable to pay penalty of a sum of up to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to anything contained in sub-section (5), it shall be open to the Corporation to`
  line `proceed against a director or any other employee who had entered into such contract or arrangement in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this section for recovery of any loss sustained by it as a result of such`
  line `contract or arrangement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of sections 4B and 4C, the expression body corporate shall include`
  line `a company, a body corporate as defined under clause (11) of section 2 of the Companies Act, a firm, a`
  line `financial institution or a scheduled bank or a public sector enterprise established or constituted by or under any Central Act or State Act, and any other incorporated association of persons or body of`
  line individuals.
obj_root_law_sections_4_c:
  sectionId (55911)
  sectionNo 4C
  orderNo 7
  title `Related party transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 130, ibid., for section 4 (w.e.f. 29-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55911&sectionno=4C&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[4C. Related party transactions.(1) Except with the consent of the Board and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, the Corporation shall not enter into any contract or arrangement with a`
  line `related party with respect to`
  line
  line `(a) sale, purchase or supply of any goods or materials;`
  line
  line `(b) selling or otherwise disposing of, or buying, property of any kind;`
  line
  line `(c) leasing of property of any kind;`
  line
  line `(d) availing or rendering of any services;`
  line
  line `(e) appointment of any agent for purchase or sale of goods, materials, services or property;`
  line
  line `(f) such related partys appointment to any office or place of profit in the Corporation, its`
  line `subsidiary or associate company;`
  line
  line `(g) underwriting the subscription of any securities, or derivatives thereof, of the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no contract or arrangement involving transactions exceeding such sums as the`
  line `Board may specify, shall be entered into except with the prior approval in the general meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no member shall vote in such general meeting to approve any contract or`
  line `arrangement which may be entered into by the Corporation, if such member is a related party:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any transactions entered into by the`
  line `Corporation in its ordinary course of business, other than transactions which are not on an arm's`
  line `length basis:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the requirement of approval under the first proviso shall not be applicable for`
  line `transactions entered into between the Corporation and`
  line
  line `(a) its wholly owned subsidiary, if any, whose financial statements are consolidated with the`
  line `Corporation and placed before the members at the general meeting for adoption;`
  line
  line `(b) a Government company, or the Central Government, or any State Government, or any`
  line `combination thereof, in respect of contract or arrangement entered into between them.`
  line
  line `Explanation.In this sub-section,`
  line
  line `(a) the expression office or place of profit means any office or place`
  line
  line `(i) where such office or place is held by a director, if the director holding it receives from`
  line `the Corporation anything by way of remuneration over and above the remuneration to which`
  line `he is entitled as director, by way of salary, fee, commission, perquisites, any rent-free`
  line `accommodation, or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(ii) where such office or place is held by an individual other than a director or by any`
  line `firm, private company or other body corporate, if the individual, firm, private company or`
  line `body corporate holding it receives from the Corporation anything by way of remuneration,`
  line `salary, fee, commission, perquisites, any rent-free accommodation, or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression arm's length transaction means a transaction between two related parties`
  line `that is conducted as if they were unrelated, so that there is no conflict of interest.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall formulate a policy on materiality of related party transactions and on dealing with`
  line `related party transactions, including clear threshold limits, and shall review and update such policy at`
  line `least once in every three years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that a transaction with a related party`
  line `shall be considered material if the amount of the transaction to be entered into, individually or taken`
  line `together with previous transactions during a financial year, exceeds such percentage of the annual`
  line `consolidated turnover of the Corporation as per its last audited financial statements as may be specified in`
  line `any regulation made by the Securities and Exchange Board in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Every contract or arrangement entered into under sub-section (1) shall be referred to in a report`
  line `made by the Board to the members, along with the justification for entering into such contract or`
  line arrangement.
  line
  line `(4) Where any contract or arrangement is entered into by a director or any other employee, without`
  line `obtaining the consent of the Board or approval by a resolution in the general meeting under sub-section`
  line `(1) and if it is not ratified by the Board or, as the case may be, by the members at a meeting within three`
  line `months from the date on which such contract or arrangement was entered into, such contract or`
  line `arrangement shall be voidable at the option of the Board or, as the case may be, of the members and if the`
  line `contract or arrangement is with a related party to any director, or is authorised by any other director, the`
  line `directors concerned shall indemnify the Corporation against any loss incurred by it.`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to anything contained in sub-section (4), it shall be open to the Corporation to`
  line `proceed against a director or any other employee who had entered into such contract or arrangement in`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this section for recovery of any loss sustained by it as a result of such`
  line `contract or arrangement.`
  line
  line `(6) Any director or any other employee of the Corporation who had entered into or authorised a`
  line `contract or arrangement in violation of the provisions of this section, shall be liable to pay penalty of a`
  line `sum of up to twenty-five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_d:
  sectionId (55912)
  sectionNo 4D
  orderNo 8
  title `Adjudication of penalties`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by s. 130, ibid., for section 4 (w.e.f. 29-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55912&sectionno=4D&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[4D. Adjudication of penalties.—(1) The Central Government may, by an order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint an officer of the Central Government, not below the rank of Joint Secretary to`
  line `the Government of India or equivalent, as adjudicating officer for adjudging penalties under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating officer may, on a complaint made in writing by a person authorised by the`
  line `Corporation, and after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by an order impose penalty on a`
  line `director or employee liable to penalty under any provision of this Act on account of any contravention or`
  line `violation on his part.`
  line
  line `(3) The adjudicating officer, for the purposes of discharging his functions under this Act, shall have`
  line `the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while`
  line `trying a suit, to summon and enforce the attendance of any person and examine him on oath and to require`
  line `the discovery and production of documents or other electronic records, and shall be deemed to be a civil`
  line `court for purposes of Order XXI of the Civil Procedure Code, 1908.`
  line
  line `(4) A director or employee aggrieved by any order made by the adjudicating officer may prefer an`
  line `appeal to such officer to the Central Government of a rank higher than that of the adjudicating officer as`
  line `the Central Government may appoint as appellate authority, within thirty days from the date on which a`
  line `copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer is received by the aggrieved individual, and the officer`
  line `so appointed may, after giving the individual an opportunity of being heard, pass such order as he may`
  line `deem fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against, or remanding the case to the`
  line `adjudicating officer for disposal, with such directions as he may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a director or employee of the Corporation having already been subjected to penalty under`
  line `this Act for any contravention or violation of any provision of this Act, again commits such contravention`
  line `or violation within a period of three years from the date of order imposing such penalty passed by the`
  line `adjudicating officer, he shall be liable for the second or subsequent contravention or violation for twice`
  line `the amount of penalty provided therefor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4965)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 9
  title `Capital of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 .Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 131, for section 5 (w.e.f. 29-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4965&sectionno=5&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Capital of Corporation.-- (1) The authorised share capital of the Corporation shall be twenty five thousand crore rupees, divided into two thousand and five hundred crore shares of ten rupees each:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, increase the authorised share capital or`
  line `reduce the authorised share capital to such amount not less than the amount of the paid-up equity capital`
  line `of the Corporation immediately before the coming into force of section 131 of the Finance Act, 2021, as it`
  line `may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Corporation may, with the previous approval of the Central Government,`
  line `consolidate or reduce the nominal or face value of the shares, divide the authorised share capital into`
  line `equity share capital or a combination of equity and preference share capital, and divide the nominal or`
  line `face value of shares into such denomination as the Corporation may decide.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall, with the previous approval of the Central Government, issue equity shares`
  line `to the Central Government in consideration for the paid-up equity capital provided by the Central`
  line `Government to the Corporation as it stood before the coming into force of section 131 of the Finance Act,`
  line 2021.
  line
  line `(3) The share capital of the Corporation shall consist of equity shares and preference shares, which`
  line `may be fully paid-up or partly paid-up:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may determine the terms of issue of partly paid-up shares and payment of`
  line `calls for such partly paid-up shares.`
  line
  line `(4) The Corporation may from time to time increase its issued share capital, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, whether by public issue or rights issue or preferential allotment or`
  line `private placement or issue of bonus shares to existing members holding equity shares, or by issue of`
  line `shares to employees pursuant to share based employee benefits schemes, or by issue of shares to life`
  line `insurance policyholders of the Corporation, or otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall, on a fully diluted basis hold, --`
  line
  line `(a) at all times, not less than fifty-one per cent. of the issued equity share capital of the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(b) during a period of five years from the date of first issue of shares to any person other than the`
  line `Central Government, not less than seventy-five per cent. of the issued equity share capital of the`
  line `Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no shares shall be issued other than by way of rights issue unless authorised`
  line `by a special resolution, except in the circumstances where the provisions of the second and third`
  line `provisos to sub-section (1) of section 23A apply:`
  line
  line `Provided also that issue of shares to life insurance policyholders of the Corporation shall not be`
  line `by preferential allotment or private placement.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Corporation issues shares at a premium, whether for cash or otherwise, a sum equal to`
  line `the aggregate amount of the premium received on those shares shall be transferred to a share premium`
  line `account, and the provisions of sub-sections (7) and (8) shall, except as provided in sub-section (6), apply`
  line `as if the share premium account were the paid-up share capital of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(6) The share premium account referred to in sub-section (5) may be applied by the Corporation`
  line
  line `(a) towards the issue of unissued shares of the Corporation to members as fully paid-up bonus`
  line shares;
  line
  line `(b) in writing off the expenses of, or the commission paid or discount allowed on, any issue of`
  line `shares or debentures of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) in providing for the premium payable on the redemption of any redeemable preference shares`
  line `or of any debentures or of any securities of the Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(d) for the purchase of its own shares or other securities.]`
  line
  line `(7) The Corporation may, by a special resolution, reduce its paid-up equity share capital in the`
  line `following manners, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) giving of previous notice by the Corporation of the intended reduction to every member, and`
  line `to such class or classes of creditors as the Central Government may, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(b) constitution of a committee which shall consist of a chairperson who has been a judge of a`
  line `High Court or the chairperson of a tribunal and such independent experts not exceeding two as the`
  line `Board may appoint, to consider representations, if any, that may be made by members and creditors`
  line `referred to in clause (a) in respect of the intended reduction and to submit its recommendations to the`
  line `Board; and`
  line
  line `(c) after consideration of the committees recommendations, making of recommendations by the`
  line `Board for reduction, either as given in the notice or with such modifications as the Board may`
  line `consider necessary, to the Central Government for its approval.`
  line
  line `(8) Without prejudice to the generality of the power under sub-section (7), the Corporation may`
  line `reduce its paid-up equity share capital by`
  line
  line `(a) extinguishing or reducing the liability on any of its equity shares in respect of share capital not`
  line `paid-up; or`
  line
  line `(b) cancelling, with or without extinguishing or reducing liability on any of its paid-up equity`
  line `shares, any paid-up equity share capital which is either lost or is unrepresented by available assets; or`
  line
  line `(c) paying off, with or without extinguishing or reducing liability on any of its paid-up equity`
  line `shares, any paid-up equity share capital which is in excess of the wants of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force--`
  line
  line `(a) regarding various categories of persons in favour of whom an issuer may make reservations`
  line `on a competitive basis, in relation to a public issue, the Corporation may, at any time during the`
  line `period of five years from the commencement of section 131 of the Finance Act, 2021, make a`
  line `reservation on a competitive basis, to an extent of up to ten per cent. out of the issue size, in favour of`
  line `its life insurance policyholders as one of the reserved categories for such public issue:`
  line
  line `Provided that the value of the allotment of equity shares to such a policyholder shall not exceed`
  line `two lakh rupees, or such higher amount as the Central Government may by notification specify:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, in the event of under-subscription in the policyholder reservation portion,`
  line `the unsubscribed portion may be allotted on a proportionate basis, in excess of the value referred to in`
  line `the first proviso, subject to the total allotment to a policyholder not exceeding five lakh rupees or such`
  line `higher amount as the Central Government may by notification specify:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the policyholders in favour of whom reservation is made under this sub-section`
  line `may be offered shares at a price not lower than by more than ten per cent. of the price at which net`
  line `offer to public is made to other categories of applicants;`
  line
  line `(b) regarding ineligibility for computation of minimum promoters contribution, in relation to a`
  line `public issue by way of an initial public offer, all equity shares of the Corporation held by the Central`
  line `Government, including all shares acquired during the period of three years preceding the opening of`
  line `such public offer, resulting from a bonus issue or otherwise, shall be eligible for such computation;`
  line
  line `(c) requiring the holding of paid-up equity shares by the sellers for a minimum holding period as`
  line `a condition for offering such shares for sale to the public, in relation to a public issue by way of an`
  line `initial public offer, all fully paid-up equity shares of the Corporation held by the Central Government`
  line `shall be eligible for such an offer for sale:`
  line
  line `Provided that and subject to any regulation made by the Securities and Exchange Board, no`
  line `shares issued by the Corporation against revaluation of assets or by utilisation of revaluation reserves`
  line `or from unrealised profits shall be eligible for computation of minimum promoters contribution and`
  line `for offer for sale in relation to a public issue by way of initial public offer.`
  line
  line `Explanation. Words and expressions used in this sub-section but not defined either in this Act`
  line `or in the Insurance Act or in the Companies Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in regulations made by the Securities and Exchange Board regarding issue of capital and`
  line `disclosure requirements, to the extent not repugnant with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(10) The Corporation may issue other securities, including bonds, debentures, notes, commercial`
  line `paper and other debt instruments, for the purpose of raising funds to meet its business requirements.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (55913)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 10
  title `Transferability of shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 131, for section 5 (w.e.f. 29-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55913&sectionno=5A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Transferability of shares.--(1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-sections (2) and (3), the`
  line `shares of the Corporation shall be freely transferable:`
  line
  line `Provided that any arrangement between two or more persons in respect of transfer of shares shall be`
  line `enforceable as a contract.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall entitle the Central Government to transfer any shares`
  line `held by it in the Corporation, if as a result of such transfer, the shares held by it, on a fully diluted basis,`
  line `shall reduce to less than fifty-one per cent. of the issued equity share capital of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) No person, other than the Central Government, acting individually or with persons acting in`
  line `concert with such person, or constituents of a group, shall hold equity share in excess of five per cent. of`
  line `issued equity share capital of the Corporation, or such higher percentage as the Central Government may`
  line `by notification specify.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,-`
  line
  line `(a) the expression group shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Competition Act, 2002 (12`
  line `of 2003);`
  line
  line `(b) the expression persons acting in concert shall have the meaning assigned to it in regulations`
  line `made by the Securities and Exchange Board regarding substantial acquisition of shares and takeovers.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (55914)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 11
  title `Register of members, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 131, for section 5 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55914&sectionno=5B&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. Register of members, etc.--(1) The Corporation shall keep and maintain the following registers,`
  line `in such form and in such manner as may be specified by regulations, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) register of members, indicating separately each class of equity and preference shares held by`
  line `each member residing in or outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) register of debenture-holders; and`
  line
  line `(c) register of any other security holders.`
  line
  line `(2) Every register maintained under sub-section (1) shall include an index of the names included`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(3) The register and index of beneficial owners maintained by a depository under section 11 of the`
  line `Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) shall be deemed to be the corresponding register and index for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) No notice of any trust, whether express or implied or constructive, shall be entered on the register`
  line `of members or be receivable by the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a depository in respect of shares held by it as a`
  line `registered owner on behalf of the beneficial owners.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section and section 5C, the expressions beneficial owner,`
  line `depository and registered owner shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clauses (a),`
  line `(e) and (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_c:
  sectionId (55915)
  sectionNo 5C
  orderNo 12
  title `Declaration in respect of beneficial interest in shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 131, for section 5 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).br`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55915&sectionno=5C&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[5C. Declaration in respect of beneficial interest in shares.—(1) Where the name of a person is`
  line `entered on the register of members of the Corporation as the holder of shares in the Corporation but he`
  line `does not hold beneficial interest in such shares, such person shall make, within such time and in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed for a company under section 89 of the Companies Act, a declaration to the`
  line `Corporation specifying the name and other particulars of the person who holds beneficial interest in such`
  line shares.
  line
  line `(2) Every person who holds or acquires a beneficial interest in shares of the Corporation shall make,`
  line `within such time and in such form as may be prescribed for a company under section 89 of the Companies`
  line `Act, a declaration to the Corporation specifying the nature of his interest, particulars of the person in`
  line `whose name the share stands registered in the books of the Corporation and such other particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed under the said section.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any change occurs in the beneficial interest in shares of the Corporation, the person`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) and the beneficial owner specified in sub-section (2) shall, within a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date of such change, make a declaration to the Corporation in such form and`
  line `containing such particulars as may be prescribed for a company under section 89 of the Companies Act.`
  line
  line `(4) No right in relation to any share in respect of which a declaration is required to be made under this`
  line `section but has not been made by the beneficial owner, shall be enforceable by him or by any person`
  line `claiming through him.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section, beneficial interest in a share includes, directly or indirectly,`
  line `through any contract, arrangement or otherwise, the right or entitlement of a person alone or together with`
  line `any other person to—`
  line
  line `(a) exercise or cause to be exercised any or all of the rights attached to such share; or`
  line
  line `(b) receive or participate in any dividend or other distribution in respect of such share.`
  line
  line `(6) Every individual who, acting alone or together or through one or more persons, holds beneficial`
  line `interests, of not less than twenty-five per cent. or such other percentage as may be prescribed for a`
  line `company under section 90 of the Companies Act, in the shares of the Corporation or the right to exercise,`
  line `or the actual exercising of significant influence or control as defined in clause (27) of section 2 of the`
  line `Companies Act, over the Corporation (herein referred to as “significant beneficial owner”), shall make a`
  line `declaration to the Corporation, specifying the nature of his interest and other particulars, in such manner`
  line `and within such period of acquisition of the beneficial interest or rights and any change thereof, as may be`
  line `prescribed for a company under section 90 of the Companies Act.`
  line
  line `(7) The Corporation shall maintain a register of the interest declared by individuals under sub-section (6) and changes therein, which shall include the name of individual, his date of birth, address, details of`
  line `ownership in the Corporation and such other details as may be prescribed for a company under section 90`
  line `of the Companies Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_d:
  sectionId (55916)
  sectionNo 5D
  orderNo 13
  title `Shares to be securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 131, for section 5 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55916&sectionno=5D&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[5D. Shares to be securities.—Notwithstanding anything contained in the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) or any other law for the time being in force, the shares of the`
  line `Corporation shall be deemed to be securities as defined under the said Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_e:
  sectionId (55917)
  sectionNo 5E
  orderNo 14
  title `Right of registered members to nominates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 131, for section 5 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55917&sectionno=5E&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[5E. Right of registered members to nominate.—(1) Every individual registered member may, at`
  line `any time, nominate, in such manner as may be specified by regulations, an individual to whom all his`
  line `rights in the shares shall vest in the event of death of such member.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the shares are registered in the name of more than one individual jointly, the joint holders`
  line `may together nominate, in such manner as may be specified by regulations, an individual to whom all`
  line `their rights in the shares shall vest in the event of the death of all such joint holders.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for time being in force or in any disposition,`
  line `whether testamentary or otherwise, where a nomination in respect of shares is made and which purports to`
  line `confer on the nominee the right to vest the shares, the nominee shall, on the death of the member or, as`
  line `the case may be, on the death of all the joint holders, become entitled to all the rights of the member or, as`
  line `the case may be, of all the joint holders, in relation to such shares, and all other persons shall be excluded`
  line `unless the nomination has been varied or cancelled before death in such manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(4) Where the nominee is a minor, it shall be lawful for the individual registered holder of the shares`
  line `to make nomination to appoint, in such manner as may be specified by regulations, any person to become`
  line `entitled to the shares in the event of his death during the minority of the nominee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4966)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 15
  title `Functions of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4966&sectionno=6&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the rules, if any, made by the Central Government`
  line `in this behalf, it shall be the general duty of the Corporation to carry on life insurance business, whether`
  line `in or outside India, and the Corporation shall so exercise its powers under this Act as to secure that life`
  line `insurance business is developed to the best advantage of the community.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub-section (1) but subject to the`
  line `other provisions contained in this Act, the Corporation shall have power--`
  line
  line `(a) to carry on capital redemption business, annuity certain business or reinsurance business in so`
  line `far as such reinsurance business appertains to life insurance business;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the rules, if any, made by the Central Government in this behalf, to invest the funds`
  line `of the Corporation in such manner as the Corporation may think fit and to take all such steps as may`
  line `be necessary or expedient for the protection or realisation of any investment; including the taking`
  line `over of and administering any property offered as security for the investment until a suitable`
  line `opportunity arises for its disposal;`
  line
  line `(c) to acquire, hold and dispose of any property for the purpose of its business;`
  line
  line `(d) to transfer the whole or any part of the life insurance business carried on outside India to any`
  line `other person or persons, if in the interest of the Corporation it is expedient so to do;`
  line
  line `(e) to advance or lend money upon the security of any movable property or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(f) to borrow or raise any money in such manner and upon such security as the Corporation may`
  line `think fit;`
  line
  line `(g) to carry on either by itself or through any subsidiary any other business in any case where`
  line `such other business was being carried on by a subsidiary of an insurer whose controlled business has`
  line `been transferred to and vested in the Corporation under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) to carry on any other business which may seen to the Corporation to be capable of being`
  line `conveniently carried on in connection with its business and calculated directly or indirectly to render`
  line `profitable the business of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(i) to do all such things as may be incidental or conducive to the proper exercise of any of the`
  line `powers of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) In the discharge of any of its functions the Corporation shall act so far as may be on business`
  line principles.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (4967)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to impose conditions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by 52 of 1975, s. 41 (w.e.f. 16-2-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4967&sectionno=6A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Power to impose conditions, etc.-- (1) In entering into any arrangement, under section 6, with`
  line `any concern, the Corporation may impose such conditions as it may think necessary or expedient for`
  line `protecting the interest of the Corporation and for securing that the accommodation granted by it is put to`
  line `the best use by the concern.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any arrangement entered into by the Corporation under section 6 with any concern`
  line `provides for the appointment by the Corporation of one or more directors of such concern, such provision`
  line `and any appointment of directors made in pursuance thereof shall be valid and effective notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force or in the memorandum, articles of association or any other instrument relating to the`
  line `concern, and any provision regarding share, qualification, age limit, number of directorships, removal`
  line `from office of directors and such like conditions contained in any such law or instrument aforesaid, shall`
  line `not apply to any director appointed by the Corporation in pursuance of the arrangement as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) Any director appointed as aforesaid shall--`
  line
  line `(a) hold office during the pleasure of the Corporation and may be removed or substituted by any`
  line `person by order in writing by the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director or for anything done`
  line `or omitted to be done in good faith in the discharge of his duties as a director or anything in relation`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(c) not be liable to retirement by rotation and shall not be taken into account for computing the`
  line `number of directors liable to such retirement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4968)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 17
  title `Transfer of assets and liabilities of existing insurers carrying on controlled business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4968&sectionno=7&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) On`
  line `the appointed day there shall be transferred to and vested in the Corporation all the assets and liabilities`
  line `appertaining to the controlled business of all insurers.`
  line
  line `(2) The assets appertaining to the controlled business of an insurer shall be deemed to include all`
  line `rights and powers, and all property, whether movable or immovable, appertaining to his controlled`
  line `business, including, in particular, cash balances, reserve funds, investments, deposits and all other`
  line `interests and rights in or arising out of such property as may be in the possession of the insurer and all`
  line `books of account or documents relating to the controlled business of the insurer; and liabilities shall be`
  line `deemed to include all debts, liabilities and obligations of whatever kind then existing and appertaining to`
  line `the controlled business of the insurer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The expression "assets appertaining to the controlled business of an insurer"--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to a composite insurer, includes that part of the paid-up capital of the insurer or`
  line `assets representing such part which has or have been allocated to the controlled business of the`
  line `insurer in accordance with the rules made in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to a Government, means the amount lying to the credit of that business on the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any such assets are subject to any trust referred to in sub-section (6) of section 27 of the`
  line `Insurance Act or to any other trust for the benefit of policy-holders, the assets shall be deemed to have`
  line `vested in the Corporation free from any such trust.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4969)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 18
  title `Provident, superannuation and other like funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4969&sectionno=8&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an insurer whose controlled`
  line `business is to be transferred to and vested in the Corporation under section 7, has established a provident`
  line `or superannuation fund or any other like fund for the benefit of his employees and constituted a trust in`
  line `respect thereof (hereinafter in this section referred to as an existing trust), the moneys standing to the`
  line `credit of any such fund on the appointed day, together with any other assets belonging to such fund, shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), stand transferred to and vest in the Corporation on the`
  line `appointed day free from any such trust.`
  line
  line `(2) Where all the employees of any such insurer do not become employees of the Corporation under`
  line `section 11, the moneys and other assets belonging to any such fund as it referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `shall be apportioned between the trustees of the fund and the Corporation in the prescribed manner; and in`
  line `case of any dispute regarding such apportionment, the decision of the Central Government thereon shall`
  line `be final.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation shall, as soon as may be after the appointed day, constitute in respect of the`
  line `moneys and other assets which are transferred to and vested in it under this section, one or more trusts`
  line `having objects as similar to the objects of the existing trusts as in the circumstances may be practicable.`
  line
  line `(4) Where all the moneys and other assets belonging to an existing trust are transferred to and vested`
  line `in the Corporation under this section, the trustees of such trust, shall as from the appointed day, be`
  line `discharged from the trust, expect as respects things done or omitted to be done before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4970)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 19
  title `General effect of vesting of controlled business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4970&sectionno=9&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise expressly provided by or`
  line `under this Act, all contracts, agreements and other instruments of whatever nature subsisting or having`
  line `effect immediately before the appointed day and to which an insurer whose controlled business has been`
  line `transferred to and vested in the Corporation is a party or which are in favour of such insurer shall in so far as they relate to the controlled business of the insurer be of as full force and affect against or in favour of`
  line `the Corporation, as the case may be, and may be enforced or acted upon as fully and effectually as if,`
  line `instead of the insurer, the Corporation had been a party thereto or as if they had been entered into or`
  line `issued in favour of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) If on the appointed day any suit, appeal or other legal proceeding of whatever nature is pending by`
  line `or against an insurer, then, in so far as it relates to his controlled business, it shall not abate, be`
  line `discontinued or be in any way prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer to the Corporation of the`
  line `business of the insurer or anything done under this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be`
  line `continued, prosecuted and enforced by or against the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4971)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 20
  title `Provisions as to composite insurers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4971&sectionno=10&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the removal of doubts it is hereby declared that in`
  line `any case where an insurer whose controlled business has been transferred to an vested in the corporation`
  line `under this Act is a composite insurer, the provisions of the preceding sections shall only apply to the`
  line `extent to which any property appertains to his controlled business and to rights and powers acquired, and`
  line `to debts, liabilities and obligations incurred, and to contracts, agreements and other instruments made by`
  line `the insurer for the purposes of his controlled business and to legal proceedings relating to those purposes,`
  line `and the provisions of those sections shall be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by rules made in this behalf provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for the determination of the question whether any property appertains to his controlled`
  line `business or whether any rights, powers, debts, liabilities or obligations were acquired or incurred or`
  line `any contract, agreement or other instrument was made by the insurer for the purposes of his`
  line `controlled business or whether any documents relate to those purposes;`
  line
  line `(b) for the allocation of the paid-up capital or assets representing such paid-up capital, as the case`
  line `may be, between the controlled business of the insurer and any other business;`
  line
  line `(c) for substituting for any agreements entered into by any insurer partly for the purposes of his`
  line `controlled business and partly for other purposes separate agreements in the requisite terms and for`
  line `any apportionments and indemnities consequent thereon;`
  line
  line `(d) for the severance of leases comprising property of which part only is transferred to and vested`
  line `in the Corporation by virtue of this Act and for apportionment consequent on such severance;`
  line
  line `(e) for the apportionment and the making of financial adjustments with respects to any debts,`
  line `liabilities of obligations incurred by any such insurer partly for the purposes of his controlled business`
  line `and partly for other purposes and for any necessary variation of mortgages and encumbrances relating`
  line `to such debts, liabilities or obligations;`
  line
  line `(f) for the apportionment of the moneys and other assets belonging to any provident or`
  line `superannuation fund or any other like fund to which the provisions of section 8 do not apply between`
  line `persons employed in connection with the controlled business of an insurer and other persons;`
  line
  line `(g) for any other matters supplementary to or consequential on the matters aforesaid for which`
  line `provision appears to be necessary or expedient.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be laid for not less than thirty days before both Houses of`
  line `Parliament as soon as possible after they are made, and shall be subject to such modifications as`
  line `Parliament may make during the session in which they are so laid or the session immediately following.`
  line
  line `(4) Where at any time before the expiration of six months from the appointed day a question has`
  line `arisen under this section or under any rules made thereunder as to whether any property is or was held or`
  line `used by the insurer for the purposes of his controlled business, the question shall be referred to the`
  line `Tribunal for decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4972)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 21
  title `Transfer of service of existing employees of insurers to the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4972&sectionno=11&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `whole-time employee of an insurer whose controlled business has been transferred to and vested in the`
  line `Corporation and who was employed by the insurer wholly or mainly in connection with his controlled`
  line `business immediately before the appointed day shall, on and from the appointed day, become an`
  line `employee of the Corporation, and shall hold his office therein by the same tenure, at the same remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to`
  line `pension and gratuity and other matters as he would have held the same on the appointed day if this Act`
  line `had not been passed, and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment in the Corporation is`
  line `terminated or until his remuneration, terms and conditions are duly altered by the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any such employee who has, by`
  line `notice in writing given to the Central Government prior to the appointed day, intimated his intention of`
  line `not becoming an employee of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Where the Central Government is satisfied that for the purpose of securing uniformity in the`
  line `scales of remuneration and the other terms and conditions of service applicable to employees of insurers`
  line `whose controlled business has been transferred to, and ^2[vested in the Corporation], it is necessary so to`
  line `do, or that, in the interests of the Corporation and its policy-holders, a reduction in the remuneration`
  line `payable, or a revision of the other terms and conditions of service applicable, to employees or any class of`
  line `them is called for, the Central Government may, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), or`
  line `in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any other law for the time being in force, or in any`
  line `award, settlement or agreement for the time being in force, alter (whether by way of reduction or`
  line `otherwise) the remuneration and the other terms and conditions of service to such manner as it thinks fit;`
  line `and if the alteration is not acceptable to any employee, the Corporation may terminate his employment by`
  line `giving him compensation equivalent to three months remuneration unless the contract of service with`
  line `such employee provides for a shorter notice of termination.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The compensation payable to an employee under this sub-section shall be in addition`
  line `to, and shall not affect, any pension, gratuity provident fund money or any other benefit to which the`
  line `employee may be entitled under his contract of service.]`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises as to whether any person was a whole time employee of an insurer or as to`
  line `whether any employee was employed wholly or mainly in connection with the controlled business of an`
  line `insurer immediately before the appointed day the question shall be referred to the Central Government`
  line `whose decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any employee of an insurer to the`
  line `Corporation shall not entitle any such employee to any compensation under that Act or other law, and no`
  line `such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 1957, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 6-6-1957).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1957, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for “vested in it” (w.e.f. 17-9-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4973)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 22
  title `Transfer of services of existing employees of chief agents of insurers to the Corporation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4973&sectionno=12&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as the Central Government may make in this behalf, every`
  line `whole-time salaried employee of a chief agent of an insurer whose controlled business has been`
  line `transferred to and vested in the Corporation and,--`
  line
  line `(a) who was employed by the chief agent wholly or mainly in connection with the controlled`
  line `business of the insurer;`
  line
  line `(b) whose salary on the appointed day did not exceed five hundred rupees per mensem; and`
  line
  line `(c) who was in the employment of the chief agent for a continuous period of not less than one`
  line `year immediately before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, become, an employee of the Corporation and the provisions of`
  line `section 11 shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such employee as they apply in relation to a`
  line `whole-time employee of the insurer:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply except in cases where the chief agent of the insurer was`
  line `required under the terms of his contract with the insurer to render the prescribed services to policy holders`
  line `of the insurer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a whole-time salaried employee of a chief agent who has been`
  line `retrenched by the chief agent on or after the 19th day of January, 1956, the provisions of this section shall`
  line `apply as if for the words 'the appointed day' the words and figures 'the 19th day of January, 1956' had`
  line `been substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4974)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 23
  title `Duty to deliver possession of property and documents relating thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4974&sectionno=13&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `property appertaining to the controlled business of an insurer has been transferred to and vested in the`
  line `Corporation under this Act, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) every person, in whose possession, custody or control any such property may be, shall deliver`
  line `the property to the corporation forthwith;`
  line
  line `(b) any person who, on the appointed day, has in his possession, custody or control any books,`
  line `documents or other papers relating to such controlled business shall be liable to account for the said`
  line `books, documents and papers to the Corporation, and shall deliver them to the Corporation or to such`
  line `person as the Corporation may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, all the assets of an insurer appertaining to life insurance business held in deposit by`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India under the Insurance Act or by trustees in trust shall be delivered to the`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the other provisions contained in this section, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Corporation to take all necessary steps for securing possession of all properties which have been`
  line `transferred to and vested in it under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4975)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power of Corporation to modify contracts of life insurance in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4975&sectionno=14&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The corporation`
  line `may, having regard to the financial condition on the appointed day of any insurer whose controlled`
  line `business has been transferred to an vested in the Corporation, reduce the amounts of insurance under`
  line `contracts of life insurance entered into by such insurer before the 19th day of January, 1956, in such`
  line `manner and subject to such conditions as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such reduction shall be made except in accordance with a scheme prepared by the`
  line `Corporation in this behalf and approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4976)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 25
  title `Right of Corporation to seek relief in respect of certain transactions of the insurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4976&sectionno=15&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where an insurer whose controlled business has been transferred to and vested in the Corporation under`
  line `this Act has, at any time within five years before the 19th day of January, 1956,--`
  line
  line `(a) made any payment to any person without consideration;`
  line
  line `(b) sold or disposed of any property of the insurer without consideration or for an inadequate`
  line consideration;
  line
  line `(c) acquired any property or rights for an excessive consideration;`
  line
  line `(d) entered into or varied any agreement so as to require an excessive consideration to be paid or`
  line `given by the insurer;`
  line
  line `(e) entered into any other transaction of such an onerous nature as to cause a loss to, or impose a`
  line `liability on, the insurer exceeding any benefit accruing to the insurer;`
  line
  line `(f) if a composite insurer, transferred any property from his life department to his general`
  line `department without consideration or for an inadequate consideration;`
  line
  line `and the payment, sale, disposal, acquisition, agreement or variation thereof or other transaction or transfer`
  line `was not reasonably necessary for the purpose of the controlled business of the insurer or was made with`
  line `an unreasonable lack of prudence on the part of the insurer, regard being had in either case to the`
  line `circumstances at the time, the Corporation may apply for relief to the Tribunal in respect of such`
  line `transaction, and all parties to the transaction shall, unless the Tribunal otherwise directs, be made parties`
  line `to the application.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal may make such order against any of the parties to the application as it thinks just`
  line `having regard to the extent to which those parties were respectively responsible for the transaction or`
  line `benefited from it and all the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an application is made to the Tribunal under this section is respect of any transaction and`
  line `the application is determined in favour of the Corporation, the Tribunal shall have exclusive jurisdiction`
  line `to determine any claims outstanding in respect of the transaction.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (4977)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 26
  title `Compensation for acquisition of controlled business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4977&sectionno=16&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the controlled business of an`
  line `insurer has been transferred to and vested in the Corporation under this Act, compensation shall be given`
  line `by the Corporation to that insurer in accordance with the principles contained in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount of the compensation to be given in accordance with the aforesaid principles shall be`
  line `determined by the Corporation in the first instance, and if the amount so determined is approved by the`
  line `Central Government it shall be offered to the insurer in full satisfaction of the compensation payable to`
  line `him under this Act, and if, on the other hand, the amount so offered is not acceptable to the insurer he`
  line `may within such time as may be prescribed for the purpose have the matter referred to the Tribunal for`
  line decision.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (4978)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 27
  title `Constitution of Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4978&sectionno=17&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may for the purposes of this Act`
  line `constitute one or more Tribunals and each of the Tribunals shall consist of three members appointed by`
  line `the Central Government one of whom shall be a person who is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court or`
  line `has been a Judge of the Supreme Court, and he shall be the Chairman thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) A Tribunal may choose one or more persons possessing special knowledge of any matter relating`
  line `to any case under inquiry to assist the Tribunal in determining any question which has to be decided by it`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Tribunal shall have the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own procedure and decide all matters within its`
  line `competence, and may review any of its decisions in the event of there being a mistake on the face of the`
  line `record or correct any arithmetical or clerical error therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4979)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offices, branches and agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2012, s. 3, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 31-3-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4979&sectionno=18&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The central office of the Corporation shall be at such place`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall establish a zonal office at each of the following places, namely, Bombay,`
  line `Calcutta, Delhi, Kanpur and Madras, and, subject to the previous approval of the Central Government,`
  line `may establish such other zonal offices as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The territorial limits of each zone shall be such as may be specified by the Corporation.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) There may be established as many divisional offices and branches in each zone as may be`
  line `decided by the Corporation in accordance with the guidelines issued by the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority established under the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority`
  line `Act, 1999 (41 of 1999) in this regard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4980)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 29
  title `Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 132, for section 19 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4980&sectionno=19&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Executive Committee.—(1) The Board may constitute an Executive Committee of the`
  line `Board, consisting of—`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Executive;`
  line
  line `(ii) Managing Directors;`
  line
  line `(iii) the director referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 4; and`
  line
  line `(iv) four directors nominated by the Board from amongst the directors referred to in clauses (e),`
  line `(f) and (g) of sub-section (2) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee of the Board shall exercise such powers as the Board may entrust to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (55918)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 30
  title `Investment Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 132, for section 19 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55918&sectionno=19A&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Investment Committee.The Board may, for such functions relating to investment of the`
  line `funds of the Corporation as the Board may entrust, constitute an Investment Committee of the Board,`
  line `consisting of the Chief Executive and not more than seven other directors, of which a minimum two shall`
  line `be directors other than directors appointed under clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 4:`
  line
  line `Provided that the officers of the Corporation heading the functions dealing with finance, risk,`
  line `investment and law as well as its Appointed Actuary shall be invited to every meeting of the Committee`
  line `and shall have a right to be heard at the meeting.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 24B, Appointed Actuary means the`
  line `actuary appointed as such by the Corporation under the regulations made by the Authority under the`
  line `Insurance Act regarding appointed actuaries.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_b:
  sectionId (55919)
  sectionNo 19B
  orderNo 31
  title `Nomination and Remuneration Committee`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 132, for section 19 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55919&sectionno=19B&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[19B. Nomination and Remuneration Committee.(1) The Board shall constitute a Nomination`
  line `and Remuneration Committee of the Board, consisting of three or more directors from amongst directors`
  line `other than those appointed either under sub-clause (i) of clause (a) or under clause (b) or under clause (c)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 4, out of whom not less than one-half shall be independent directors at any`
  line `time when the number of independent directors in office is sufficient to constitute such proportion of the`
  line `membership of the Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson may be appointed as a member of the Nomination and Remuneration`
  line `Committee but shall not chair the Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the event of the Corporation applying to list its equity shares under any`
  line `regulation made by the Securities and Exchange Board in this behalf, the Corporation shall ensure that the`
  line `proportion of independent directors on the Nomination and Remuneration Committee shall be in`
  line `accordance with the requirements as provided under those regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Nomination and Remuneration Committee shall`
  line
  line `(i) formulate the criteria for determining qualifications, positive attributes and independence of a`
  line `director to be appointed under clause (e) or clause (f) or clause (g) of sub-section (2) of section 4 and`
  line `recommend the same to the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) in accordance with the criteria referred to in clause (i), identify individuals who are qualified`
  line `to be appointed as such a director:`
  line
  line `Provided that while identifying individuals, the Committee shall have due regard to the`
  line `requirements under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 19C;`
  line
  line `(iii) give its recommendations to the Board regarding appointment and removal of such an`
  line `individual, and carry out evaluation of his performance; and`
  line
  line `(iv) recommend to the Board a policy relating to the sum payable as sitting fees to a director`
  line `nominated or appointed under clauses (e) or (f) or (g) of sub-section (2) of section 4, subject to such`
  line `fees not exceeding such limit as may apply in respect of sitting fees payable to a director of a`
  line `company under the Companies Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_c:
  sectionId (55920)
  sectionNo 19C
  orderNo 32
  title `Audit Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 132, for section 19 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55920&sectionno=19C&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_19_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[19C. Audit Committee.—(1) The Board shall constitute an Audit Committee of the Board,`
  line `consisting of a minimum of three directors with independent directors forming a majority when the`
  line `number of independent directors in office is sufficient to constitute such proportion of the membership of`
  line `the Audit Committee:`
  line `Provided that a majority of directors on the Audit Committee, including its chairperson, shall be`
  line `individuals with ability to read and understand financial statements and at least one individual shall have`
  line `accounting or related financial management expertise:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the event of the Corporation applying to list its equity shares under any`
  line `regulation made by the Securities and Exchange Board in this behalf, the Corporation shall ensure that the`
  line `proportion of independent directors on the Audit Committee shall be in accordance with the requirements`
  line `as provided under those regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Audit Committee shall act in accordance with the terms of reference specified by the Board,`
  line `which shall include, inter alia,—`
  line
  line `(a) recommendations for appointment, remuneration and terms of appointment of the auditors of`
  line `the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) review and monitoring of the independence and performance of the auditors, and the`
  line `effectiveness of the audit process;`
  line
  line `(c) examination of financial statements and auditor’s report thereon;`
  line
  line `(d) prior approval of transactions of the Corporation with related parties:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Audit Committee may make omnibus approval for related party transactions`
  line `proposed to be entered into by the Corporation subject to the conditions specified in sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of transaction other than transactions referred to in section 4C, and`
  line `where the Audit Committee does not approve a transaction, it shall make its recommendations to the`
  line `Board:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case any transaction involving any amount not exceeding one crore rupees is`
  line `entered into by a director or an officer of the Corporation without obtaining the approval of the Audit`
  line `Committee and it is not ratified by the Audit Committee within three months from the date of the`
  line `transaction, such transaction shall be voidable at the option of the Corporation with the approval of`
  line `the Audit Committee and if the transaction is with the related party to any director or is authorised by`
  line `any other director, the director concerned shall indemnify the Corporation against any loss incurred`
  line `by it;`
  line
  line `(e) scrutiny of inter-corporate loans and investments;`
  line
  line `(f) valuation of undertakings or assets of the Corporation, wherever it is necessary;`
  line
  line `(g) evaluation of internal financial controls and risk management systems;`
  line
  line `(h) monitoring the end use of funds raised through public offers, and related matters.`
  line
  line `(3) The Audit Committee may grant omnibus approval for related party transactions proposed to be`
  line `entered into by the Corporation, subject to the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Audit Committee shall lay down the criteria for granting omnibus approval in line with the`
  line `policy referred to in sub-section (2) of section 4C including in respect of transactions which are`
  line `repetitive in nature;`
  line
  line `(b) the Audit Committee shall satisfy itself that omnibus approval is needed and that such`
  line `approval is in the interest of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) the omnibus approval shall specify the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the details regarding the name of the related party and the nature, period and the maximum`
  line `amount of the transactions that shall be entered into;`
  line
  line `(ii) the details regarding indicative base price or current contracted price, along with the`
  line `formula, if any, for variation in the price; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other conditions as the Audit Committee may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the need for related party transaction cannot be foreseen and the said`
  line `details are not available, the Audit Committee may grant omnibus approval for such transactions`
  line `subject to their value not exceeding one crore rupees per transaction;`
  line
  line `(d) the Audit Committee shall review on a quarterly basis, the details of related party transactions`
  line `entered into by the Corporation pursuant to every omnibus approval given; and`
  line
  line `(e) omnibus approval shall be valid for a period not exceeding one year and shall require fresh`
  line `approval after expiry of one year.`
  line
  line `(4) The Audit Committee may call for the comments of the auditors about internal control systems,`
  line `the scope of audit including the observations of the auditors, and review of financial statements before`
  line `their submission to the Board, and may also discuss any related issues with the auditors and the`
  line `management of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(5) The Audit Committee shall have authority to investigate any matter in relation to the items`
  line `specified in sub-section (2) or referred to it by the Board and, for this purpose, shall have the power to`
  line `obtain professional advice from external sources and have full access to information contained in the`
  line `records of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(6) The auditors of the Corporation and such key managerial personnel as the Board may specify shall`
  line `have a right to be heard in the meetings of the Audit Committee when it considers the auditor’s report.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_d:
  sectionId (55921)
  sectionNo 19D
  orderNo 33
  title `Other Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 132, for section 19 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55921&sectionno=19D&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_19_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[19D. Other Committees.—The Board may constitute such other Committees of the Board as it may`
  line `deem fit, to render advice to the Board on such matters as may be generally or specially referred to them,`
  line `and to perform such duties as the Board may entrust to them.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4981)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 34
  title `Managing Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 133, for section 20 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4981&sectionno=20&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Chief Executive and Managing Directors.(1) The Chief Executive shall, subject to the`
  line `superintendence, control and direction of the Board, be entrusted with substantial powers of management`
  line `in respect of the whole of the affairs of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Executive shall also perform such other duties in relation to the affairs of the`
  line `Corporation as the Board may entrust to him from time to time and shall, for this purpose, exercise such`
  line `powers as may be conferred upon him by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may also empower the Chief Executive to entrust or delegate such of his`
  line `duties and powers, as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Managing Director, subject to the general control of the Chief Executive, shall perform`
  line `such duties and exercise such powers as may be entrusted or delegated to him by the Board or, under subsection (2), by the Chief Executive.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4982)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 35
  title `Corporation to be guided by the directions of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4982&sectionno=21&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `In the discharge of its`
  line `functions under this Act, the Corporation shall be guided by such directions in matters of policy involving`
  line `public interest as the Central Government may give to it in writing; and if any question arises whether a`
  line `direction relates to a matter of policy involving public interest the decision of the Central Government`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4983)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 36
  title `Zonal Managers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4983&sectionno=22&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may entrust the superintendence and direction of the`
  line `affairs and business of a zonal office to ^1[an employee of the Corporation other than a whole-time`
  line `director], who shall be known as the`
  line `Zonal Manager and the Zonal Manager shall perform all such functions of the Corporation as may be`
  line `delegated to him with respect to the area within the jurisdiction of the zonal office.`
  line
  line ^2*****.
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation shall constitute in the prescribed manner for each zonal office an Employees and`
  line `Agents Relations Committee consisting of such number of persons as it thinks fit and every such`
  line `Committee shall consist of representatives of the Corporation and of its employees and agents, so`
  line `however, that the number of representatives of the employees and agents on the Committee shall not be`
  line `less than the number of representatives of the Corporation and it shall be duty of the Committee to advise`
  line `the Zonal Manager on matters which relate to the welfare of the employees and agents of the Corporation`
  line `or which are likely to promote and secure amity and good relations between them and the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 134, ibid., for a person whether a member or not (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 13 of 2021, s. 134 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4984)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 37
  title `Staff of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4984&sectionno=23&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of enabling it to discharge its functions under this`
  line `Act, the Corporation may employ such number of persons as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person employed by the Corporation or whose services have been transferred to the`
  line `Corporation under this Act, shall be liable to serve anywhere in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (55922)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 38
  title `Annual general meeting and other general meetings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 135, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-6-2021)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55922&sectionno=23A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Annual general meeting and other general meetings.—(1) An annual general meeting or`
  line `other general meeting of members shall be held in each financial year at such time as the Board may`
  line `specify, at the central office of the Corporation or at such other place in India as the Central Government`
  line `may permit on the recommendations of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that not more than fifteen months shall elapse between the date of one annual general`
  line `meeting of the Corporation and that of the next:`
  line
  line `Provided further that notwithstanding anything contained in this section, general meeting shall be`
  line `held only when the Corporation has members other than the Central Government who are entitled to vote:`
  line
  line `Provided also that until the first annual general meeting or other general meeting is held, the Board`
  line `shall perform all the functions required to be performed in such meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The members present at an annual general meeting shall be entitled to—`
  line
  line `(a) discuss the financial statements of the Corporation as referred to in section 24B and the`
  line `auditor’s report as referred to in section 25B, which shall be accompanied by the report of the`
  line `Board as referred to in section 24C, and to adopt the financial statements, along with all the`
  line `documents which are required to be attached to such financial statements under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) discuss and adopt the Annual Report prepared under section 27;`
  line
  line `(c) approve a declaration of dividend under sub-section (1) of section 28B;`
  line
  line `(d) approve the appointment of directors under sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) approve the appointment of auditors under sub-sections (1) and (4) of section 25 and fix`
  line `their remuneration under sub-section (7) of section 25.`
  line
  line `(3) Every member shall be entitled to attend a general meeting, whether in person or by proxy or by`
  line `duly authorised representative:`
  line
  line `Provided that every director shall also be entitled to attend a general meeting, whether in person or`
  line `through electronic means:`
  line
  line `Provided further that all notices of, and other communications relating to, any general meeting shall`
  line `be forwarded to the auditor appointed for the Corporation, and such auditor shall, unless exempted by the`
  line `Corporation, attend any general meeting either in person or through authorised representative who is`
  line `qualified to be an auditor, and shall have the right to be heard at such meeting on any part of the business`
  line `which concerns him as the auditor.`
  line
  line `(4) A member who is entitled to vote may exercise his vote at a general meeting in person or by proxy`
  line `or by duly authorised representative.`
  line
  line `(5) Persons entitled to attend and to exercise vote at a general meeting may also do so through`
  line `electronic means, and the manner of attendance and exercise of vote shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) No business other than that specified in sub-section (2) shall be transacted or discussed at the`
  line `annual general meeting, except with the consent of the Chairperson, unless not less than six weeks’ notice`
  line `of the same has been given to the Chairperson either by the Central Government or by at least hundred`
  line `members who have the right to vote at the meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided that such a notice shall be in the form of a definite resolution to be put to the meeting, and`
  line `that such resolution shall be included in the notice of the meeting.`
  line
  line `(7) Save and except with the consent of the Chairperson, no business other than that for which a`
  line `general meeting has been convened shall be transacted or discussed at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(8) No general meeting shall be proceeded with and no business shall be transacted at any general`
  line `meeting unless members constitute such quorum as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a meeting could not be held for want of quorum, it may be adjourned and held in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) The Corporation shall cause the minutes of all proceedings of general meetings to be entered in`
  line `books kept for that purpose.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (4985)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 39
  title `Funds of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.by Act 13 of 2021, s. 136, for section 24 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4985&sectionno=24&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[24. Funds of the Corporation.—(1) The Corporation shall have its own fund or funds, and all`
  line `receipts of the Corporation shall be credited thereto and all payments of the Corporation shall be made`
  line `therefrom:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, in relation to any of the funds of the Corporation or otherwise, establish`
  line `reserves which may or may not be allocated for a specific purpose, and such sums as the Board may`
  line `determine, may be transferred to or from such reserves.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall, for every financial year after the financial year in which the provisions of section`
  line `136 of the Finance Act, 2021 come into force, cause to be maintained—`
  line
  line `(a) a participating policyholders fund, to which all receipts from participating policyholders shall`
  line `be credited and from which all payments to such policyholders shall be made; and`
  line
  line `(b) a non-participating policyholders fund, to which all receipts from non-participating`
  line `policyholders shall be credited and from which all payments to such policyholders shall be made:`
  line
  line `Provided that the members, by resolution in a general meeting, may exempt maintenance of such`
  line `funds for one financial year at a time up to two financial years..`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (55923)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 40
  title `Books of account, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.by Act 13 of 2021, s. 136, for section 24 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55923&sectionno=24A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. Books of account, etc.---(1) The Corporation shall prepare and keep at its central office books`
  line `of account and other relevant books and records and financial statement for every financial year which`
  line `give a true and fair view of the state of its affairs, including that of its zonal offices, and which explain the`
  line `transactions effected both at the central office and at its zonal offices.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall prepare and keep at each zonal office of the Corporation, books of account`
  line `and other relevant books and records and financial statement for every financial year which give a true`
  line `and fair view of the state of affairs of every divisional office established in the zone corresponding to such`
  line `zonal office and which explain the transactions effected thereat.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation shall prepare and keep at each divisional office of the Corporation, books of`
  line `account and other relevant books and records and financial statement for every financial year which give`
  line `a true and fair view of the state of affairs of every branch established under such divisional office and`
  line `which explain the transactions effected thereat.`
  line
  line `(4) All or any of the books of account and other relevant books and records referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) may be kept at such other place or places in India as the Board`
  line `may decide.`
  line
  line `(5) The Corporation shall be deemed to have complied with the provisions of sub-section (1) or subsection (2) or sub-section (3), in respect of a zonal office or a divisional office, other than the central`
  line `office, or a branch of the Corporation, whether within or outside India, if proper books of account relating`
  line `to the transactions effected at such office or branch, are kept thereat and proper summarised returns are`
  line `sent periodically to the central office or the corresponding zonal office or the corresponding divisional`
  line `office, or to the other place referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) The books of account and other relevant books and records referred to in sub-section (1) or subsection (2) or sub-section (3) may be kept in electronic form, in such manner as the Board may determine.`
  line
  line `(7) The books of account of the Corporation relating to a period of not less than ten financial years`
  line `immediately preceding a financial year, together with the vouchers relevant to any entry in such books of`
  line `account, shall be kept in good order:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government has appointed a special auditor under section 25D or is`
  line `of the opinion that circumstances exist which render it necessary so to do, it may direct the Corporation`
  line `that the books of account be kept for such longer period as the Central Government may specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_b:
  sectionId (55924)
  sectionNo 24B
  orderNo 41
  title `Financial statements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.by Act 13 of 2021, s. 136, for section 24 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55924&sectionno=24B&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[24B. Financial statements.(1) The financial statements of the Corporation shall give a true and`
  line `fair view of the state of affairs of the Corporation and shall be in conformity with applicable accounting`
  line `requirements as may be applicable for such financial statements:`
  line
  line `Provided that the financial statements shall not be treated as not disclosing a true and fair view of the`
  line `state of affairs of the Corporation, merely by reason of the fact that they do not disclose any matters`
  line `which are not required to be disclosed by this Act or by the Insurance Act or by the Insurance Regulatory`
  line `and Development Authority Act, 1999 (42 of 1999) or by any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) At every annual general meeting, the Board shall place before such meeting financial statements`
  line `for the preceding financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation shall, in addition to financial statements provided under sub-section (2), prepare`
  line `a consolidated financial statement of the Corporation in conformity with the requirements referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), and shall place the same before the annual general meeting, along with the placing of its`
  line `financial statements under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Corporation shall also attach along with its financial statements, a separate`
  line `statement containing the salient features of the consolidated financial statement.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this Act applicable to financial statements under sub-section (1) and under`
  line `section 24C, the inquiry by the auditor into matters referred to in and making of the auditors report on`
  line `accounts under section 25B, and adoption of financial statements under section 23A at the annual general`
  line `meeting, shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the consolidated financial statement referred to in sub-section`
  line `(3).`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (3), where the financial`
  line `statements are not in conformity with the standards applicable thereto, the Corporation shall disclose in`
  line `the financial statements the deviation from applicable standards, the reasons therefor and the financial`
  line `effects, if any, arising out of such deviation.`
  line
  line `(6) Financial statements including consolidated financial statement, if any, shall be approved by the`
  line `Board before they are signed on behalf of the Board by two whole-time directors, one director other than`
  line `a whole-time director, the heads of the finance and secretarial functions of the Corporation and its`
  line `Appointed Actuary, for submission to the auditor for his report thereon.`
  line
  line `(7) The auditors report shall be attached to every financial statement.`
  line
  line `(8) A signed copy of every financial statement, including consolidated financial statement, if any,`
  line `shall be issued, circulated or published, along with a copy each of--`
  line
  line `(a) any notes annexed to or forming part of such financial statement;`
  line `(b) the auditor's report; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Board's report referred to in sub-section (1) of section 24C.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_c:
  sectionId (55925)
  sectionNo 24C
  orderNo 42
  title `Board's report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.by Act 13 of 2021, s. 136, for section 24 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55925&sectionno=24C&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_24_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[24C. Board’s report.—(1) There shall be attached to financial statements placed before general`
  line `meeting, a report by the Board, which shall include—`
  line
  line `(a) number of meetings of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) a Directors’ Responsibility Statement;`
  line
  line `(c) details in respect of frauds reported by auditors;`
  line
  line `(d) a statement on declarations given by independent directors under the second proviso to subsection (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) the Corporation’s policy on directors’ appointment, including the criteria for determining`
  line `qualifications, positive attributes and independence of a director, which are referred to in section 19B;`
  line
  line `(f) explanations or comments by the Board on every qualification, reservation or adverse remark`
  line `or disclaimer made in the auditor’s report;`
  line
  line `(g) particulars in respect of investments in terms of the provisions of section 27A of the Insurance`
  line `Act as made applicable to the Corporation by notification issued under sub-section (2) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(h) particulars of contracts or arrangements with related parties, referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4C;`
  line
  line `(i) the state of the Corporation’s affairs;`
  line
  line `(j) the amounts, if any, which are carried to any reserves;`
  line
  line `(k) the amount, if any, which it recommends should be paid by way of dividend;`
  line
  line `(l) material changes and commitments, if any, affecting the financial position of the Corporation,`
  line `which have occurred between the end of the financial year to which the financial statements relate`
  line `and the date of the report;`
  line
  line `(m) a statement indicating the manner in which annual evaluation of the performance of`
  line `individual directors has been made under section 19B;`
  line
  line `(n) such other matters as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where disclosures referred to in this sub-section have been included in the financial`
  line `statements, such disclosures may be referred to instead of being repeated in the Board’s report:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the policy referred to in clause (e) is made available on the`
  line `Corporation’s website, it shall be sufficient compliance of the requirement under the said clause if the`
  line `salient features of the policy and any changes therein are specified in brief in the Board’s report and`
  line `the web-address at which the policy is available is indicated therein.`
  line
  line `(2) The Directors’ Responsibility Statement referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall state`
  line that—
  line
  line `(a) in the preparation of the annual accounts, the requirements referred to in section 24B were`
  line `followed, along with proper explanation relating to material departures;`
  line
  line `(b) accounting policies were selected and applied consistently and the judgments made and`
  line `estimates were reasonable and prudent, so as to give a true and fair view of the state of affairs of the`
  line `Corporation at the end of the financial year and of the profit and loss of the Corporation for that`
  line period;
  line
  line `(c) proper and sufficient care for the maintenance of adequate accounting records was taken in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act for safeguarding the assets of the Corporation and for`
  line `preventing and detecting fraud and other irregularities;`
  line
  line `(d) the annual accounts were prepared on a going concern basis;`
  line
  line `(e) the vigilance administration referred to in clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 8 of the`
  line `Central Vigilance Commission Act, 2003 (45 of 2003) was in operation in the Corporation under the`
  line `superintendence of the Central Vigilance Commission, and in addition, internal financial controls to`
  line `be followed by the Corporation had been laid down and were operating effectively; and`
  line
  line `(f) proper systems were devised to ensure compliance with the provisions of applicable laws and`
  line `were operating effectively.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression “internal financial controls”`
  line `means the policies and procedures adopted for ensuring the orderly and efficient conduct of the`
  line `Corporation’s business, including adherence to its policies, safeguarding of its assets, prevention and`
  line `detection of errors, accuracy and completeness of accounting records, and timely preparation of`
  line `reliable financial information.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board’s report and any annexures thereto under sub-section (1) shall be signed on behalf`
  line `of the Board by two whole-time directors and one director other than a whole-time director.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_d:
  sectionId (55926)
  sectionNo 24D
  orderNo 43
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.by Act 13 of 2021, s. 136, for section 24 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55926&sectionno=24D&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_24_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[24D. Penalties.—If the Chief Executive or the Managing Director in charge of finance or the head of`
  line `the finance function of the Corporation or any other person of the Corporation charged by the Board with`
  line `the duty of complying with the provisions of section 24A or section 24B or section 24C contravenes any`
  line `of the said provisions, such Chief Executive or Managing Director or head of finance function or other`
  line `person shall, for each section whose provisions have been contravened, be liable to pay penalty of a sum`
  line `which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (4986)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 44
  title `Appointment of auditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 137, for section 25 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4986&sectionno=25&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall, at its first annual general meeting,`
  line `appoint as many auditors (which may be individual or firm) as it deems fit, and such auditor shall hold`
  line `office from the conclusion of that meeting till the conclusion of its sixth annual general meeting`
  line `thereafter, and shall similarly appoint auditor for subsequent periods of five years at a time, and the`
  line `manner and procedure of selection of auditors by the members at such a meeting shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before such appointment is made, the written consent of the auditor to such`
  line `appointment, and a certificate from the auditor that the appointment, if made, shall be in accordance with`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed, shall be obtained from the auditor:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such certificate shall also declare that the auditor satisfies the criteria provided`
  line `for eligibility for appointment as an auditor of a company under section 141 of the Companies Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall not appoint an auditor for more than one term of five consecutive years:`
  line
  line `Provided that an auditor who has completed the term of appointment shall not be eligible for reappointment or for fresh appointment as auditor for a period of five years from such completion:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no audit firm shall be appointed as auditor for a period of five years which, if`
  line `appointed, as on the date of its appointment, would have a common partner or partners with the audit firm`
  line `whose term as auditor in the Corporation had expired in the financial year immediately preceding the`
  line `financial year in which fresh appointment is to be made, or which is associated with the same network of`
  line `audit firms as the audit firm whose term had expired as aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided also that nothing contained in this sub-section shall prejudice the right of the Corporation to`
  line `remove an auditor or the right of the auditor to resign from such office of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression same network includes firms`
  line `operating or functioning under a common brand name or trade name, or under common control, or which`
  line `are network firms as defined under any guidelines for networking issued by the Institute of Chartered`
  line `Accountants of India, constituted under section 3 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949).`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Corporation may resolve in a general meeting to provide`
  line that--
  line
  line `(a) in the audit firm appointed by it, the auditing partner and his team shall be rotated at such`
  line `intervals as may be resolved by members;`
  line
  line `(b) the audit shall be conducted by more than one auditor.`
  line
  line `(4) Any casual vacancy in the office of an auditor shall be filled by the Board within thirty days, but if`
  line `such casual vacancy is as a result of the resignation of an auditor, such appointment shall also be`
  line `approved by the Corporation in a general meeting convened within three months of the Board making`
  line `recommendations in this behalf, and the auditor so appointed shall hold office till the conclusion of the`
  line `next annual general meeting.`
  line
  line `(5) Where at any annual general meeting, no auditor is appointed, the existing auditor shall continue`
  line `to be the auditor of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(6) All appointments, including the filling of a casual vacancy of an auditor under this section, shall`
  line `be made after taking into account the recommendations of the Audit Committee.`
  line
  line `(7) The remuneration of the auditor shall be fixed in the general meeting or in such manner as may be`
  line `determined therein.`
  line
  line `(8) Until the first annual general meeting is held, auditors duly qualified to act as auditors of`
  line `companies under the law for the time being in force relating to companies shall be appointed by the Board`
  line `with the previous approval of the Central Government, and shall receive such remuneration from the`
  line `Corporation as the Central Government may fix.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an auditor has been appointed`
  line `previous to the first annual general meeting, either under section 25 as it stood before the coming into`
  line `force of section 137 of the Finance Act, 2021 or thereafter under sub-section (8), and the term specified`
  line `for such auditor's appointment has not expired, and the auditor meets the criteria referred to in subsection (1), such auditor shall continue till the expiry of the term so specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section or in section 25A shall prejudice the right of the`
  line `Corporation to remove such auditor or the right of the auditor to resign from such office of the`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(10) An auditor appointed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (8) or sub-section (9) shall provide to`
  line `the Corporation or its subsidiaries such other services as are approved by the Board, but shall not include`
  line `any of the services, whether rendered directly or indirectly, that are enumerated in section 144 of the`
  line `Companies Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that an auditor who has been performing any non-audit services on or before the coming`
  line `into force of section 137 of the Finance Act, 2021 shall comply with the provisions of this sub-section`
  line `before the close of the first financial year in which the said section comes into force.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the word firm shall include a limited liability`
  line `partnership incorporated under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (55927)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 45
  title `Removal and resignation of auditor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 137, for section 25 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55927&sectionno=25A&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Removal and resignation of auditor.—(1) The auditor appointed under section 25 may be`
  line `removed from office before expiry of the term of appointment only by a special resolution:`
  line
  line `Provided that before taking any action under this sub-section, an auditor proposed to be removed shall`
  line `be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard, which shall include the right to represent in writing to`
  line `the Corporation and, where the auditor requests that such representation be notified to members, to have a`
  line `copy thereof sent to every member and in case a copy is not sent as aforesaid because it was received too`
  line `late, to have the representation read out at the meeting, without prejudice to the right to be heard orally.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditor who has resigned from the Corporation shall file within a period of thirty days from`
  line `the date of resignation, a statement in the prescribed form with the Corporation, indicating the reasons and`
  line `other facts as may be relevant with regard to the resignation.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to any action under this Act or any other law, if the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor General of India, that any change of auditor is`
  line `required, it may make an order that the auditor shall not function as such and may appoint another auditor`
  line `in place of such auditor.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_b:
  sectionId (55928)
  sectionNo 25B
  orderNo 46
  title `Powers and duties of auditors and auditor's report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 137, for section 25 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55928&sectionno=25B&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[25B. Powers and duties of auditors and auditor’s report.—(1) Every auditor of the Corporation`
  line `shall have a right of access at all times to the books of account and vouchers of the Corporation, and shall`
  line `be entitled to require from the officers of the Corporation such information and explanation as the auditor`
  line `may consider necessary for the performance of his duties as auditor, and shall, amongst other matters,`
  line `inquire into the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) whether loans and advances made by the Corporation on the basis of security have been`
  line `properly secured;`
  line
  line `(b) whether the terms on which loans and advances have been made are prejudicial to the interests`
  line `of the Corporation or its members;`
  line
  line `(c) whether transactions of the Corporation which are represented merely by book entries are`
  line `prejudicial to its interests;`
  line
  line `(d) whether so much of the assets of the Corporation as consist of shares, debentures and other`
  line `securities have been sold at a price less than that at which they were purchased;`
  line
  line `(e) whether loans and advances made by the Corporation have been shown as deposits;`
  line
  line `(f) whether personal expenses have been charged to revenue account;`
  line
  line `(g) where it is stated in the books and documents of the Corporation that any shares have been`
  line `allotted for cash, whether cash has actually been received in respect of such allotment, and if no cash`
  line `has actually been so received, whether the position as stated in the account books and the balancesheet is correct, regular and not misleading:`
  line
  line `Provided that the auditor shall also have the right of access to the records of all the subsidiaries and`
  line `associate companies of the Corporation, in so far as they relate to consolidation of the Corporation’s`
  line `financial statements with those of such subsidiaries and associate companies.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditor shall make a report to the members on the accounts examined by the auditor and on`
  line `every financial statement which is required by or under law to be placed in general meeting, and such`
  line `report shall, after taking into account applicable provisions of this Act and any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, the standards referred to in section 24B, and matters that are required to be included in the`
  line `audit report under the provisions of this Act or any other law for the time being in force, and to the best of`
  line `the information and knowledge of the auditor, state that the said accounts and financial statements give a`
  line `true and fair view of the state of the Corporation’s affairs as at the end of its financial year and profit or`
  line `loss and cash flow for the year.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditor’s report shall also state—`
  line
  line `(a) whether the auditor has sought and obtained all the information and explanations which to the`
  line `best of the auditor’s knowledge and belief were necessary for the purpose of audit and if not, the`
  line `details thereof and the effect of such information on the financial statements;`
  line
  line `(b) whether, in the auditor’s opinion, proper books of account as required by law have been kept`
  line `by the Corporation so far as appears from the auditor’s examination of those books and proper returns`
  line `adequate for the purposes of audit have been received from branches not visited by the auditor;`
  line
  line `(c) whether any report referred to in the proviso to sub-section (6) has been sent to the`
  line `Corporation’s auditor, and the manner in which the Corporation’s auditor has dealt with it in`
  line `preparing the auditor’s report;`
  line
  line `(d) whether the Corporation’s balance-sheet and profit and loss account dealt within the report are`
  line `in agreement with the books of account and returns;`
  line
  line `(e) whether, in the auditor’s opinion, the financial statements comply with applicable standards;`
  line
  line `(f) the observations or comments of the auditor on financial transactions and matters which have`
  line `any adverse effect on the functioning of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(g) whether any director is disqualified to be or remain a director under clause (i) of section 4A;`
  line
  line `(h) any qualification, reservation or adverse remark relating to the maintenance of accounts and`
  line `matters connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(i) whether the Corporation has adequate internal financial controls with reference to financial`
  line `statements in place and the operating effectiveness of such controls;`
  line
  line `(j) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any of the matters required to be included in the audit report under this section is answered`
  line `in the negative or with a qualification, the report shall state the reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(5) All qualifications, observations or comments mentioned in the report of the auditor appointed for`
  line `the Corporation, in respect of financial transactions or matters that have any adverse effect on the`
  line `functioning of the Corporation, shall be read out in general meeting and shall be open to inspection by`
  line `any member.`
  line
  line `(6) In respect of a branch or an office of the Corporation, the accounts shall be audited either by the`
  line `auditor appointed for the Corporation (herein referred to as Corporation’s auditor) in this section or by`
  line `any other person qualified for appointment as an auditor of the Corporation and appointed as such under`
  line `section 25, or where the branch or office is situated in a country outside India, the accounts of the branch`
  line `or office shall be audited either by the Corporation’s auditor or by an accountant or by any other person`
  line `duly qualified to act as an auditor of the accounts of the branch or office in accordance with the laws of`
  line `that country, and the duties and powers of the Corporation’s auditor with reference to the audit of the`
  line `branch or office and the auditor thereof, if any, shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the auditor for a branch or office shall prepare a report on the accounts of the branch or`
  line `office, examined by such auditor and shall send it to the Corporation’s auditor, who shall deal with it in`
  line `the Corporation’s auditor’s report in such manner as the Corporation’s auditor may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_c:
  sectionId (55929)
  sectionNo 25C
  orderNo 47
  title `Internal auditor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 137, for section 25 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55929&sectionno=25C&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_25_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[25C. Internal auditor.—(1) The Board shall, on the recommendation of the Audit Committee,`
  line `appoint an internal auditor, who shall either be a chartered accountant or a cost accountant, or such other`
  line `professional as may be determined by the Board to conduct the internal audit of the functions and`
  line `activities of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Audit Committee shall—.`
  line
  line `(a) recommend to the Board for the appointment, remuneration and terms of appointment of the`
  line `internal auditor;.`
  line
  line `(b) in consultation with the internal auditor, formulate the scope, functioning, periodicity and`
  line `methodology for conducting the internal audit;.`
  line
  line `(c) review and monitor the internal auditor’s performance and effectiveness of audit process.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_d:
  sectionId (55930)
  sectionNo 25D
  orderNo 48
  title `Special auditor`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 137, for section 25 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55930&sectionno=25D&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_25_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[25D. Special auditor.—Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 19C, 23A, 25, 25A and 25B,`
  line `the Central Government may, at any time, appoint such auditor as it deems fit as a special auditor to`
  line `examine and report on the accounts of the Corporation, and such auditor shall have the same rights of`
  line `access to the books of account and vouchers of the Corporation and entitlement to require information and`
  line `explanation from the officers of the Corporation as an auditor of the Corporation has under section 25B.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (4987)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 49
  title `Actuarial valuations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4987&sectionno=26&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[The Board] shall, ^2[every year], cause an investigation to be made by`
  line `actuaries into the financial conditions of the ^3[life insurance business of the Corporation, including a`
  line `valuation of the liabilities of the Corporation in respect thereto], and submit the report of the actuaries to the ^4[Board].`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 .Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 138, for "The Corporation" (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2012, s. 4, for "once at least in every two years" (w.e.f. 31-3-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 1965, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 29-9-1965).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by 13 of 2021, s. 138, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (4988)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 50
  title `Annual report of activities of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4988&sectionno=27&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall, as soon as may be, after`
  line `the end of each financial year, prepare and submit to the Central Government in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed a report giving an account of its activities during the previous financial year, ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and the report shall also give an account of the activities, if any, which are likely to be undertaken by the`
  line `Corporation in the next financial year" omitted by s. 139, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (4989)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 51
  title `Surplus from life insurance business, how to be utilised.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 140, ibid., for section 28 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4989&sectionno=28&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[28. Surplus from life insurance business, how to be utilized.--.(1) If as a result of any`
  line `investigation undertaken by the Board under section 26, any surplus emerges, --`
  line
  line `(a) for every financial year previous to the financial year for which the funds referred to in subsection (2) of section 24 are to be maintained, and for any subsequent financial year for which`
  line `members may exempt the maintenance of such funds,--`
  line
  line `(I) ninety per cent., or such higher percentage as the Board may approve, of such surplus shall`
  line `be allocated to or reserved for the life insurance policyholders of the Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(II) such percentage of the remaining surplus as the Board may approve, shall be allocated to`
  line `or reserved for members and may either be credited to a separate account maintained by the`
  line `Corporation or be transferred to such reserve or reserves as the Board may specify;`
  line
  line `(b) for every financial year other than that referred to in clause (a),-`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of participating policyholders,--`
  line
  line `(I) ninety per cent., or such higher percentage as the Board may approve, of surplus`
  line `relating to such policyholders, shall be transferred to the participating policyholders fund, and`
  line `shall be allocated to or reserved for the life insurance participating policyholders of the`
  line `Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(II) such percentage of the remaining surplus as the Board may approve, shall be`
  line `allocated to or reserved for members and may either be credited to a separate account`
  line `maintained by the Corporation or be transferred to such reserve or reserves as the Board may`
  line specify;
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of non-participating policyholders, one hundred per cent. of surplus relating to`
  line `such policyholders shall be allocated to or reserved for members and may either be credited to a`
  line `separate account maintained by the Corporation or be transferred to such reserve or reserves as the`
  line `Board may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The remaining surplus referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) or in item (ii)`
  line `of sub-clause (i) of clause (b) of sub-section (1), as the case may be, and the surplus referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (b) of sub-section (1), and the profits allocated to or reserved for the members under`
  line `section 28A, shall be utilised for such purposes as the Board may approve, including for the purpose of`
  line `declaration or payment of dividend, the issue of fully paid-up bonus shares to members and crediting any`
  line `of the reserves that the Board may create for any purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation shall, with the approval of the Board, publish on its website its surplus`
  line `distribution policy at least once in five years, or such shorter period not less than three years as the Board`
  line `may deem fit, and such policy shall specify, among other things, the percentages referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (4990)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 52
  title `Profits from any business (other than life insurance business) how to be utilised.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4990&sectionno=28A&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[28A. Profits from any business (other than life insurance business) how to be utilised.--If for`
  line `any financial year profits accrue from any business (other than life insurance business) carried on by the`
  line `Corporation, then, after making provision for reserves and other matters for which provision is necessary`
  line `or expedient, the balance of such profits shall be ^2[allocated to or reserved for the members].]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1965, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-9-1965).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 141, for "paid to the Central Government" (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b:
  sectionId (55931)
  sectionNo 28B
  orderNo 53
  title `Declaration of dividend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 142, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55931&sectionno=28B&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[28B. Declaration of dividend.--(1) No dividend shall be declared or paid by the Corporation for`
  line `any financial year except out of the surpluses and profits referred to in sub-section (2) of section 28 (after`
  line `excluding any amount representing unrealised gains, notional gains or revaluation of assets and any`
  line `change in carrying amount of an asset or of a liability on measurement of the asset or the liability at fair`
  line `value) for such year arrived at after providing for depreciation, or for any previous financial year or years`
  line `arrived at after providing for depreciation and remaining undistributed, or out of both the aforesaid`
  line `surpluses and profits:`
  line
  line `Provided that no dividend shall be declared or paid by the Corporation from its reserves other than`
  line `free reserves:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no dividend shall be declared or paid by the Corporation unless any losses`
  line `carried over from previous years and any depreciation not provided for in previous years are set off`
  line `against the surpluses and profits referred to in sub-section (2) of section 28 for the financial year for`
  line `which the dividend is proposed to be declared or paid.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, during any financial year or at any time during the period from the close of a`
  line `financial year till the holding of the annual general meeting for that financial year, declare interim`
  line `dividend out of the surpluses and profits referred to in sub-section (2) of section 28 of the financial year`
  line `for which such interim dividend is sought to be declared, or out of the surpluses and profits referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) generated in the current financial year till the close of the quarter preceding the date of`
  line `declaration of such interim dividend:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the Corporation has incurred loss during the current financial year up to the`
  line `close of the quarter immediately preceding the date of declaration of interim dividend, such interim`
  line `dividend shall not be declared at a rate higher than the average of the dividends declared by the`
  line `Corporation during the immediately preceding three financial years.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of the dividend, including interim dividend, shall be deposited in a scheduled bank in`
  line `a separate account within five days from the date of declaration of such dividend.`
  line
  line `(4) No dividend shall be paid by the Corporation in respect of any share of the Corporation except to`
  line `the member in whose name such share is entered on the register of members referred to in section 5C, or`
  line `to his order, or to his banker, and shall be payable in cash and not in stock or other form of value:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to prohibit the capitalisation of the`
  line `surpluses and profits referred to in sub-section (2) of section 28 for the purpose of issuing fully paid-up`
  line `bonus shares or paying up any amount for the time being unpaid on any share held by members:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any dividend payable in cash may be paid by cheque or warrant or in any`
  line `electronic mode to the member entitled to such payment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_c:
  sectionId (55932)
  sectionNo 28C
  orderNo 54
  title `Unpaid Dividend Account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 142, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55932&sectionno=28C&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[28C. Unpaid Dividend Account.—(1) Where a dividend has been declared by the Corporation but`
  line `has not been paid or claimed within thirty days from the date of declaration to any member entitled to`
  line `payment thereof, the Corporation shall, within seven days from the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, transfer the total amount of dividend which remains unpaid or unclaimed to a special account to be`
  line `opened by the Corporation in that behalf in any scheduled bank, to be called the Unpaid Dividend`
  line Account.
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall, within a period of ninety days of making any transfer of an amount under`
  line `sub-section (1) to the Unpaid Dividend Account, prepare a statement containing the name and last known`
  line `address of, and the amount of the unpaid dividend payable to, each member entitled to such unpaid dividend, and shall place such statement on its website and on any other website as the Central`
  line `Government may specify.`
  line
  line `(3) If any default is made in transferring the total amount referred to in sub-section (1) or any part`
  line `thereof to the Unpaid Dividend Account, the Corporation shall pay, from the date of such default, interest`
  line `on so much of the amount as has not been transferred to the said account, at such rate as is specified`
  line `in section 124 of the Companies Act, and the interest accruing on such amount shall ensure to the benefit`
  line `of the members in proportion to the amount remaining unpaid to them.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person claiming to be entitled to any money transferred under sub-section (1) to the Unpaid`
  line `Dividend Account may apply to the Corporation for payment of the money claimed.`
  line
  line `(5) The amount remaining unclaimed and unpaid for a period of seven years from the date it became`
  line `due for payment in the Unpaid Dividend Account shall be transferred to the Investor Education and`
  line `Protection Fund established under sub-section (1) of section 125 of the Companies Act and shall be`
  line `deemed to be an amount credited to the said Fund under sub-section (2) of the said section.`
  line
  line `(6) All shares in respect of which dividend has not been paid or claimed for seven consecutive years`
  line `or more shall be transferred by the Corporation in the name of the Investor Education and Protection Fund`
  line `along with a statement containing such details as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that every claimant of such shares shall be entitled to claim the transfer thereof from the said`
  line `Fund in accordance with such procedure and on submission of such documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that in case any dividend is paid or`
  line `claimed for any year during the said period of seven consecutive years, the share shall not be transferred`
  line `to the Investor Education and Protection Fund.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (4991)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 55
  title `Reports to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4991&sectionno=29&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause the report of the`
  line `auditors under section 25, the report of the actuaries under section 26 and the report giving an account of`
  line `the activities of the Corporation under section 27 to be laid before both Houses of Parliament as soon as`
  line `may be after each such report is received by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (4992)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 56
  title `Corporation to have the exclusive privilege of carrying on life insurance business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4992&sectionno=30&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line Except
  line `to the extent otherwise expressly provided in this Act, on and from the appointed day the Corporation`
  line `shall have the exclusive privilege of carrying on life insurance business in India; and on and from the said`
  line `day any certificate to registration under the Insurance Act held by any insurer immediately before the said`
  line `day shall cease to have effect in so far as it authorises him to carry on life insurance business in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (4993)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 57
  title `Exclusive privilege of Corporation to cease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 31 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4993&sectionno=30A&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Exclusive privilege of Corporation to cease.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act, the exclusive privilege of carrying on life insurance business in India by the Corporation shall cease`
  line `on and from the commencement of the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999, and`
  line `the Corporation shall, thereafter, carry on life insurance business in India in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938).]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (4994)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 58
  title `Exception in the case of insurance business in respect of persons residing outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 31 and the Second Schedule, for Controller (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4994&sectionno=31&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 30 or in the Insurance Act, the Central Government may,`
  line `by order, permit any person who has made an application in that behalf, to carry on life insurance`
  line `business in India, in respect of the lives of persons ordinarily resident outside India, subject to such`
  line `restrictions and conditions as may be specified in the order and any such order shall be deemed to have`
  line `effect as if it were a certificate of registrations issued by the ^1[Authority] to such person under section 3 of`
  line `the Insurance Act in respect of that class of business.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall authorise any person permitted to carry on life insurance business`
  line `of the nature referred to in that sub-section, to insure the life of any person ordinarily resident outside`
  line `India, during any period of his temporary residence in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (4995)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power of Corporation to have official seal in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4995&sectionno=32&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation may have for`
  line `use in any zonal office, divisional office or in any office outside India an official seal which shall be a`
  line `facsimile of the common seal of the Corporation, with the addition on its fact of the name of the zonal`
  line `office, divisional office or other office where it is to be used, and any such official seal may be affixed to`
  line `any deed or document to which the Corporation is a party.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (4996)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 60
  title `Requirement of foreign laws to be complied with in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4996&sectionno=33&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Where any property or`
  line `rights appertaining to the controlled business of an insurer are transferred to and vested in the Corporation`
  line `under this Act or would be so transferred and vested but for the fact that such transfer and vesting are`
  line `governed otherwise than by the law of India, the insurer shall comply with such directions as may be`
  line `given to him by the Corporation for the purpose of securing that the ownership of the property or, as the`
  line `case may be, that the right is effectively transferred to the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (4997)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 61
  title `Revesting of certain shares vested in the Administrator General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4997&sectionno=34&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Insurance Act, all shares which have vested in the Administrator General of any State`
  line `under sub-section (8) of the section 6A of that Act and which have not been disposed of in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of that sub-section before the appointed day, shall, on payment of the amount of`
  line `expenditure, if any, incurred by the Administrator General in relation to such shares by the persons who`
  line `would have been entitled to those shares if the said sub-section had not been enacted, revest in such`
  line persons.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (4998)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 62
  title `Repatriation of assets and liabilities in the case of foreign insurers in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4998&sectionno=35&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any`
  line `insurer incorporated outside India may, before the appointed day, make an application to the Central`
  line `Government stating that among the assets appertaining to the controlled business of the insurer there are`
  line `assets brought into India by the insurer for the purpose of building up his life insurance business in India,`
  line `which, notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, should not be transferred to and vested in the`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall determine the`
  line `value of the assets of the insurer appertaining to his controlled business in existence on 31st day of`
  line `December, 1955, computed as at that date in accordance with the provisions contained in paragraph 3 of`
  line `Part B of the First Schedule, and deduct therefrom the total amount of the liabilities of the insurer`
  line `appertaining to his controlled business in existence on the 31st day of December 1955, computed as at`
  line `that date in accordance with the provisions contained in the Second Schedule; and if there is any excess,`
  line `the Central Government may, by order, direct that such assets equivalent in value to the excess as may be`
  line `specified in the order shall not be transferred to or vested in the Corporation, or where the order is made`
  line `after the appointed day, that the Corporation shall be divested of the said assets.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any insurer incorporated outside India, the Central Government may also, by order,`
  line `direct that any such liabilities in respect of life insurance policies expressed in any foreign currency issued`
  line `on the lives of persons who are not citizens of India as are specified in the order together with any such`
  line `assets necessary to meet the liabilities, as may be so specified, shall not be transferred to or vested in the`
  line `Corporation or, if the order is made after the appointed day, that the Corporation shall be divested of such`
  line `liabilities and assets as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(4) The amount of liabilities in respect of the policies referred to in an order made under`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be computed as at the 31st day of December, 1955,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case where in respect of the insurer concerned an order has been made under`
  line `sub-section (2), in accordance with the provisions contained in clause (b) of the Second schedule; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, in accordance with method A specified in the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In computing the amount of liabilities in respect of the policies referred to in this`
  line `sub-section, allowance shall be made for receipts and payments in respect of such policies from the 31st`
  line `day of December, 1955, up to the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(5) Every order made by the Central Government under this section shall be carried out by the`
  line `Corporation in such manner as the Central Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (4999)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 63
  title `Contracts of chief agents and special agents to terminate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=4999&sectionno=36&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Insurance Act or in any other law for the time being in force every contract appertaining`
  line `to controlled business subsisting immediately before the appointed day,--`
  line
  line `(a) between an insurer and his chief agent or between an insurer and a special agent; or`
  line
  line `(b) between the chief agent of an insurer and a special agent;`
  line
  line `shall, as from the appointed day, cease to have effect and all rights accruing to the chief agent or the`
  line `special agent under any such contract shall terminate on that day:`
  line
  line `Provided that in every such case compensation shall be given by the Corporation to the chief agent or`
  line `the special agent, as the case may be, in accordance with the principles contained in the Third Schedule,`
  line `and the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 16 shall, so far as may be, apply in every such case.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (5000)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 64
  title `Policies to be guaranteed by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 8 of 2012, s. 6 (w.e.f. 31-3-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5000&sectionno=37&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The sums assured by all policies issued by`
  line `the Corporation including any bonuses declared in respect thereof and, subject to the provisions contained`
  line `in section 14 the amounts assured by all policies issued by any insurer the liabilities under which have`
  line `vested in the Corporation under this Act, and all bonuses declared in respect thereof, whether before or`
  line `after the appointed day, shall be guaranteed as to payment in cash by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Corporation shall endeavour that its funds are invested in the attractive schemes`
  line `formulated by it to ensure increased bonus to policyholders while having least investment risk so as to`
  line `enable the Corporation to play a greater role in economic enrichment of the masses while maintaining its`
  line `position as a leading player in the market.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (5001)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 65
  title `Liquidation of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5001&sectionno=38&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding up of companies or`
  line `corporations shall apply to the corporation established under this Act, and the Corporation shall not be`
  line `placed in liquidation save by order of the Central Government and in such manner as that Government`
  line `may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (5002)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 66
  title `Special provisions for winding up of certain insurers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5002&sectionno=39&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Where any insurer being a company`
  line `(other than a composite insurer) whose controlled business has been transferred to and vested in the`
  line `Corporation under this Act has in accordance with the provisions of this Act collected and distributed any`
  line `moneys paid to him by the Corporation by way of compensation or otherwise and has also complied with`
  line `any direction given to him by the Corporation for the purpose of securing that the ownership of any`
  line `property or any right is effectively transferred to the Corporation, the Central Government may on`
  line `application being made to it in this behalf by such insurer grant a certificate to the insurer that there is no`
  line `reason for the continued existence of the insurer and where such a certificate has been granted shall cause`
  line `the certificate to be published in the Official Gazette and upon the publication thereof the insurer shall be`
  line dissolved.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (5003)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 67
  title `Penalty for withholding property, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5003&sectionno=40&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `If any person wilfully withholds or fails to deliver to`
  line `the Corporation as required by section 13, any property or any books, documents or other papers which`
  line `may be in his possession or unlawfully retains possession of any property of an insurer which has been transferred to and vested in the Corporation under this Act or wilfully applies any such property to`
  line `purposes other than those expressed in or authorised by this Act, he shall, on the complaint of the`
  line `Corporation, be punishable with imprisonment which may extent to one year, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (5004)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 68
  title `Tribunal to have exclusive jurisdiction in certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5004&sectionno=41&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have`
  line `jurisdiction to entertain or adjudicate upon any matter which a Tribunal is empowered to decide or`
  line `determine under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (5005)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 69
  title `Enforcement of decisions of Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5005&sectionno=42&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any decision of a Tribunal may be enforced in any`
  line `civil court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the person against whom the decision is to be`
  line `enforced actually and voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally works for gain or owns any`
  line `property, as if it were a decree passed by that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (5006)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 70
  title `Application of the Insurance Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5006&sectionno=43&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following sections of the Insurance Act shall, so far`
  line `as may be, apply to the Corporation as they apply to any other insurer, namely:--`
  line
  line `Sections 2, 2B, 3, 18, 26, 33, 38, 39, 41, 45, 46, 47A, 50, 51, 52, 110A, 110B, 110C, 119, 121,`
  line `122 and 123.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall as soon as may be after the commencement of this Act, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the following sections of the Insurance Act shall apply to`
  line `the Corporation subject to such conditions and modifications as may be specified in the notification,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `Sections 2D, 10, 11, 13, 14, 15, 20, 21, 22, 23, 25, 27A, 28A, 35, 36, 37, 40, 40A, 40B, 43, 44,`
  line `102 to 106, 107 to 110, 111, 113, 114 and 116A.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) Section 42 of the Insurance Act shall have effect in relation to the issue to any individual of a`
  line `licence to act as an agent for the purpose of soliciting or procuring life insurance business for the`
  line `Corporation as if the reference to an officer authorised by the ^2[Authority] in this behalf in sub-section (1)`
  line `thereof included a reference to an officer of the Corporation authorised by the ^2[Authority] in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, be notification in the Official Gazette, direct that all or any of the`
  line `provision of the Insurance Act other than those specified in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), shall apply`
  line `to the Corporation subject to such conditions and modifications as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Every notification issued under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) shall be laid for not less than`
  line `thirty days before both Houses of Parliament as soon as possible after it is issued, and shall be subject to`
  line `such modifications as Parliament may make during the session in which it is so laid or the session`
  line `immediately following.`
  line
  line `(5) Save as provided in this section, nothing contained in the Insurance Act shall apply to the`
  line Corporation.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 1957, s. 3 (w.e.f. 6-6-1957).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 41 of 1999, s. 1, for "Controller" (w.e.f. 19-4-2000).`
