obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `[Deduction of income-tax not to be made on interest or dividend.] Omitted by the Finance`
  line `Act, 2002 (20 of 2002), s. 157 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (5014)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 72
  title `Act not to apply in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5014&sectionno=44&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall apply in relation to--`
  line
  line `(a) any insurer whose business is being voluntarily wound up or is being wound up under the`
  line `orders of the Court;`
  line
  line `(b) any insurer to whom the Insurance Act does not apply by reason of the provisions contained`
  line `in section 2E thereof;`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply on and from the date on which the`
  line `provisions contained in section 2E of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938) shall cease to operate.]`
  line
  line `(c) any composite insurer in respect of the management of whose affairs an Administrator has`
  line `been appointed under section 52A of the Insurance Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the scheme run by the Central Government known as the Post Office Life Insurance Fund;`
  line
  line `(e) any approved superannuation fund as defined in clause (a) of section 58N of the Indian`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), which is in existence on the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(f) any scheme in existence on the appointed day or any scheme framed after the appointed day`
  line `with the approval of the Central Government whereby, in consideration of certain compulsory`
  line `deductions made by Government from the salaries of its employees as part of the conditions of`
  line `service, the payment of money is assured by Government on the death of the employee concerned or`
  line `on the happening of any contingency dependent on his life.`
  line
  line `^2[(g) any Family Pension Scheme Framed under the Coal Mines Provident Fund, Family Pension`
  line `and Bonus Schemes Act, 1948 (46 of 1948), or the Employees Provident Funds and Family Pension`
  line `Fund Act, 1952 (19 of 1952), for the purpose of providing family pension and life assurance benefits`
  line `to the employees covered by the said Scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 8 of 2012, s. 7 (w.e.f. 31-3-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 16 of 1971, s. 31 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 23-4-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (5015)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 73
  title `Special provisions regarding transfer of controlled business of certain composite insurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 1957, s. 4 (w.e.f. 6-6-1957).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5015&sectionno=45&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[45. Special provisions regarding transfer of controlled business of certain composite`
  line `insurer.--Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (c) of section 44, the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that on and with effect from such date as may be specified in`
  line `the notification the assets and liabilities appertaining to the controlled business of a composite insurer in`
  line `respect of the management of whose affairs an Administrator has been appointed under section 52A of the`
  line `Insurance Act shall be transferred to the vested in the Corporation, and on the issue of such a notification`
  line `the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such insurer and to the transfer and`
  line `vesting of the assets and liabilities of his controlled business in the Corporation as they apply in relation`
  line `to all other insurers and to the transfer and vesting of assets and liabilities of their controlled business in`
  line `the Corporation, subject to the modification that references in this Act to the appointed day shall be`
  line `construed as references to the day specified in the notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (5016)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 74
  title `Defects in constitution of Corporation or Committees or in appointment or nomination of directors not to invalidate acts or proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 143, sections 46 and 47 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5016&sectionno=46&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `^1[46. Defects in constitution of Corporation or Committees or in appointment or nomination of`
  line `directors not to invalidate acts or proceedings.—(1) No act or proceeding of the Corporation or of its`
  line `Board or any Committee thereof shall be called in question on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Corporation or the Board or such Committee, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(2) No act done by an individual as a director shall be deemed to be invalid, notwithstanding that it`
  line `was subsequently noticed that his appointment or nomination, as the case may be, was invalid by reason`
  line `of any defect or disqualification or had terminated by virtue of any provision contained in this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to give validity to any act done by such`
  line `individual as director after his appointment or nomination, as the case may be, has been noticed by the`
  line `Corporation to be invalid or to have terminated.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (5017)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 75
  title `Protection of action taken under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 143, sections 46 and 47 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5017&sectionno=47&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `^1[47. Protection of action taken under this Act.—(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any director or employee of the Corporation for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules or regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) A director who is not a whole-time director shall be held liable only in respect of such acts of`
  line `omission or commission of the Corporation which had occurred with his knowledge, attributable through`
  line `Board processes, and with his consent or connivance or where he had not acted diligently.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, the reference to “Board” shall include`
  line `Committees of the Board..`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (5018)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 76
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5018&sectionno=48&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office and the conditions of service of ^1[directors];`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) the manner of disclosure of interest by a director under section 4B;`
  line
  line `(ab) the conditions subject to which the Board may consent to related party transactions under`
  line `section 4C;`
  line
  line `(ac) the securities and instruments which may be issued under section 5;`
  line
  line `(ad) the manner of reservation in favour of life insurance policyholders and allotment against`
  line `such reservation, in relation to a public issue, under clause (a) of sub-section (9) of section 5;]`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which the moneys and other assets belonging to any such fund as is referred to`
  line `in section 8 shall be apportioned between the trustees of the fund and the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) the services which the chief agent should have rendered for the purpose of the proviso to`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `^3[(cc) the terms and conditions of service of the employees ^4*** of the Corporation, including`
  line `those who became employees ^4*** of the Corporation on the appointed day under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(d) the jurisdiction of the Tribunals constituted under section 17;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which, and the persons to whom, any compensation under this Act may be paid;`
  line
  line `(f) the time within which any matter which may be referred to a Tribunal for decision under this`
  line `Act may be so referred;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which investments may be made by the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which an Employees and Agents Relations Committee may be constituted for`
  line `each zonal office;`
  line
  line `^5[(ha) the manner in which general meetings shall be held, and the business to be transacted and`
  line `procedure to be followed thereat;`
  line
  line `(hb) the quorum for a general meeting, and the manner of holding the meeting if it could not be`
  line `held for want of quorum and was adjourned under section 23A;`
  line
  line `(hc) the manner in which persons may attend a general meeting and exercise their vote;`
  line
  line `(hd) the manner in which notices may be served on behalf of the Corporation upon members or`
  line `other persons;`
  line
  line `(he) the form and manner in which the financial statements referred to in sub-section (8) of`
  line `section 24B may be issued, circulated or published;`
  line
  line `(hf) matters that may be prescribed under clause (n) of sub-section (1) of section 24C;`
  line
  line `(hg) the manner and procedure of selection and conditions of appointment of auditors under subsection (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(hh) the form in which an auditor who has resigned shall indicate the reasons and other facts`
  line `relevant to the resignation under sub-section (2) of section 25A;`
  line
  line `(hi) the matters to be prescribed under clause (j) of sub-section (3) of section 25B;`
  line
  line `(hj) the duties and powers of the Corporations auditor with reference to the audit of a branch or`
  line `office of the Corporation and the auditor thereof, under sub-section (6) of section 25B;`
  line
  line `(hk) the details, procedure and documents under sub-section (6) of section 28C.]`
  line
  line `(i) the form in which the report giving an account of the activities of the Corporation shall be`
  line prepared;
  line
  line `(j) the conditions subject to which the Corporation may appoint employees;`
  line
  line `(k) the fees payable under this Act and the manner in which they are to be collected;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `^3[(2A) The regulations and other provisions as in force immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `Life Insurance Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1981, with respect to the terms and conditions of service`
  line `of employees and agents of the Corporation including those who became employees and agents of the`
  line `Corporation on the appointed day under this Act, shall be deemed to be rules made under clause (cc) of`
  line `sub-section (2) and shall, subject to the other provisions of this section, have effect accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2B) The power to make rules conferred by clause (cc) of sub-section (2) shall include--`
  line
  line `(i) the power to give retrospective effect to such rules; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the power to amend by way of addition, variation or repeal, the regulations and other`
  line `provision refereed to in sub-section (2A), with retrospective effect,`
  line
  line `from a date not earlier than the twentieth day of June, 1979.`
  line
  line `(2C) The provisions of clause (cc) of sub-section (2) and sub-section (2B) and any rules made under`
  line `the said clause (cc) shall have effect, and any such rule made with retrospective effect from any date shall`
  line `also be deemed to have had effect from that date, notwithstanding any judgement, decree or order of any`
  line `court, tribunal or other authority and notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes`
  line `Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or any other law or any agreement, settlement, award or other instrument for the`
  line `time being in force.]`
  line
  line `^6[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything preciously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 144,ibid., for members (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s.144, ibid., for clause (aa) (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 1 of 1981, s. 2 (w.e.f. 20-6-1979).`
  line
  line `4. The words “and agents” omitted by Act 8 of 2012, s. 8 (w.e.f. 31-3-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 144 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 52 of 1975, s. 43, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 16-2-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (5019)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 77
  title `Power to make regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=5019&sectionno=49&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Board] may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Gazette of India, make regulations not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder to provide for all matters for which provision is expedient for the`
  line `purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the powers and functions of the ^1[Board] which may be delegated to the Zonal Managers;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) the method of recruitment of employees and agents of the Corporation and the terms and`
  line `conditions of the agents;]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4** * * *`
  line
  line ;
  line
  line `(d) the territorial limits of each zone established under this Act and the business to be transacted`
  line `in each Zone;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which the ^5[fund or funds] of the Corporation shall be maintained;`
  line
  line `(f) the maintenance of separate funds and accounts at each of the zonal offices;`
  line
  line `(g) the jurisdiction of each divisional office and the establishment of Councils representative of`
  line `policy-holders in each area served by a divisional office for the purpose of advising the divisional`
  line `office in respect of any matter which may be referred to it;`
  line
  line `^6[(h) the manner in which meetings of the Board and its Committees shall be held, the business to`
  line `be transacted and procedure to be followed thereat, and the quorum therefor;]`
  line
  line `^7* * * *;`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(k) the classification of policies, whether issued by the Corporation or by any insurer whose`
  line `controlled business has been transferred to and vested in the Corporation, for the purposes of`
  line `declaring differential bonuses, wherever necessary;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner in which and the intervals within which the accounts of the various zonal offices,`
  line `divisional offices and branch offices may be inspected and their accounts audited,`
  line
  line `(m) the conditions subject to which any payment may be made by the Corporation.`
  line
  line `^9[(n) the manner of election of directors under clause (f) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner of registers to be kept and maintained under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 5B;
  line
  line `(p) the manner of nomination by an individual registered member or joint holder of shares, the`
  line `manner of variation or cancellation of such nomination, and the manner of nomination in favour of a`
  line `minor, under section 5E;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which shares, including partly paid-up`
  line `shares, may be issued, held, transferred and registered;`
  line
  line `(r) the maintenance and operation of the funds and reserves under section 24;`
  line
  line `(s) the form and manner in which the books and records referred to in section 24A may be kept;]`
  line
  line `^9[(2A) Any reference in the regulations as in force immediately before the coming into force`
  line `of section 132 of the Finance Act, 2021 to Investment Committee shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the Investment Committee of the Board referred to in section 19A.]`
  line
  line `^10[(3) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation].`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 145, for dbqstCorporationdbqst (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2012, s. 9, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 31-3-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (bb) omitted by Act 1 of 1981, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-1981).`
  line
  line `4. Clause (c) omitted by Act 13 of 2021, s. 145 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 145, ibid., for Fund (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 145, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `7. Clause (i) omitted by s. 145, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `8.Omitted by Act 8 of 2012, s. 9 (w.e.f. 31-3-2012).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 145 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 1 of 1981, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-1-1981).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (55933)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 78
  title `Form, manner, etc. for companies to apply with modifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 146 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55933&sectionno=50&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `^1[50. Form, manner, etc., for companies to apply with modifications.—Where this Act provides`
  line `that the form or manner or period or details in respect of any declaration to be made or the particulars to`
  line `be included in any register to be maintained shall be such as may be prescribed for a company under the`
  line `Companies Act, such prescribed form or manner or period or details or particulars, as the case may be,`
  line `shall apply subject to such modifications, exceptions and conditions that the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (55934)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 79
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 146 (w.e.f. 30-6-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796&sectionId=55934&sectionno=51&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00018_195631_1517807320796
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `^1[51. Power to remove difficulties.--(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act as amended by Part III of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2021, the Central Government may, by`
  line `order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this`
  line `Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of Part III of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2021.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid on the table`
  line `of each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
